Breakfast of Champions , or Goodbye Blue Monday , published in 1973 , is the seventh novel by the American author Kurt Vonnegut .
Winter of the World is written by the Welsh - born author Ken Follett , a historical novell published in 2012 is the second book in the Century Trilogy .
Aphrodite : mœurs antiques ( `` Aphrodite : ancient morals '' ) is an 1896 French - language novel by Pierre Louÿs .
Christo , Castro and Free Love is a novel by the Bulgarian writer Georgi Tenev .
Line of Delirium and Emperors of Illusions are two 1995 books of a space opera trilogy by Russian science fiction writer Sergey Lukyanenko ( Shadows of Dreams is a short prequel to Line of Delirium and is usually included in the second book ) .
The Skeptic 's Walk ( French : Promenade du Skeptique ) is a book by Denis Diderot , completed in 1747 .
Anastasia on Her Own ( 1985 ) is a young - adult novel by Lois Lowry .
The Angel Makers is a 2007 novel written by Jessica Gregson based on the true story of The Angel Makers of Nagyrév , two Hungarian women who sold arsenic to unhappily married women to kill their husbands .
The Judge and His Hangman ( German : Der Richter und sein Henker ) is a 1950 novel by the Swiss writer Friedrich Dürrenmatt .
From Nine to Nine or Between Nine and Nine ( German title : Zwischen neun und neun ; original title : Freiheit ) is a novel by Leo Perutz first published in 1918 .
The Variation of Animals and Plants under Domestication is a book by Charles Darwin that was first published in January 1868 .
The System of Nature or , the Laws of the Moral and Physical World ( Système de la Nature ou Des Loix du Monde Physique et du Monde Moral ) is a work of philosophy by Paul Henri Thiry , Baron d'Holbach ( 1723 - -1789 ) .
Rumpole and the Golden Thread is a 1982 collection of short stories by John Mortimer about defence barrister Horace Rumpole .
Robots Have No Tails is a 1952 collection of science fiction short stories by Lewis Padgett ( pseudonym of Henry Kuttner and C. L. Moore ) .
The Defence of Duffer 's Drift is a short 1904 book by Major General Sir Ernest Dunlop Swinton .
An Advancement of Learning is a crime novel by Reginald Hill , the second novel in the Dalziel and Pascoe series .
Asterix in Spain is the fourteenth volume of the Asterix comic book series , by René Goscinny ( stories ) and Albert Uderzo ( illustrations ) .
Il teatro alla moda ( The Fashionable Theater ) is a satirical pamphlet in which its author , the Venetian composer Benedetto Marcello ( 1686 - -1739 ) , vents his critical opinions on the milieu of the Italian opera seria in the first decades of the eighteenth century .
Ultimate Adventures was a six - issue comic book , written by Ron Zimmerman and drawn by Duncan Fegredo , and published by Marvel Comics .
Dave at Night is a young adult , historical fiction novel written by award - winning author Gail Carson Levine in 1999 .
The Wind Off the Small Isles is a novella by Mary Stewart , first published in 1968 .
The Deemster is a novel by Hall Caine published in 1887 , considered to be the first ' Manx novel ' .
The Land of Foam also known as At the Edge of Oikoumene ( Russian : На краю Ойкумены , Na krayu Oikumeny ) and Great Arc ( Великая Дуга , Velikaya Duga ) is a novel written by the Soviet writer Ivan Yefremov in 1946 .
( Documents Relating to ) The Sentimental Agents in the Volyen Empire is a 1983 science fiction novel by Nobel Prize in Literature - winner Doris Lessing .
The Soft Centre is a work of detective fiction by James Hadley Chase , first published in Great Britain by Robert Hale Ltd. in 1964 .
The Ballad of the Flexible Bullet is a novella by Stephen King first published in The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction in 1984 and collected in King 's 1985 collection Skeleton Crew .
An Imaginary Life is a 1978 novella written by David Malouf .
Murder at the New York World 's Fair is a novel that was published in 1938 by Phoebe Atwood Taylor writing as Freeman Dana .
Code Complete is a software development book , written by Steve McConnell and published in 1993 by Microsoft Press , urging developers to get past code - and - fix programming and the big design up front waterfall model .
Sept cavaliers is a 1993 novel by the French writer Jean Raspail .
Faery in Shadow is a fantasy novel by science fiction and fantasy author C. J. Cherryh .
Icons of Evolution is a book by Jonathan Wells , an intelligent design advocate and fellow of the Discovery Institute , which also includes a 2002 video companion .
The Coquette or , The History of Eliza Wharton is an epistolary novel by Hannah Webster Foster .
Heavenly Discourse is a collection of satirical essays by Charles Erskine Scott Wood , published in 1927 .
Design of Cities , first published in 1967 , is an illustrated account of the development of urban form , written by Edmund Bacon ( 1910 - -2005 ) , who was the Executive Director of the Philadelphia City Planning Commission from 1949 to 1970 .
The Haunting of Hiram C. Hopgood is a children 's novel written in 1987 by Eva Ibbotson .
The Mysteries of Harris Burdick is a 1984 picture book by the American author Chris Van Allsburg consisting of a series of seemingly unrelated , highly detailed images in Van Allsburg 's distinctive style .
The Alastor Cluster is the fictional setting of three of American writer Jack Vance 's novels :
A Rap on Race is a non - fiction book co - authored by writer and social critic James Baldwin and anthropologist Margaret Mead .
Riding the Iron Rooster ( 1988 ) is a travel book by Paul Theroux primarily about his travels through China in the 1980s .
Factor T is a book first published in 1956 written by the Polish writer , philosopher , filmmaker , composer and poet Stefan Themerson .
The Wizard Knight is a series of epistolary novels written by fantasy and science fiction author Gene Wolfe .
The Fireship is one of a series of nautical novels by C. Northcote Parkinson .
Stops of Various Quills is a 1895 book written by William Dean Howells .
The Malady of Death ( French : La Maladie de la mort ) is a 1982 novella by the French writer Marguerite Duras .
Thirty - Three Teeth is a crime novel by British author Colin Cotterill and published in 2005 by Soho Press , New York ( ISBN 156947429X ) .
Bitter Fruit is a novel by Achmat Dangor first published in 2001 by Kwela Books of Cape Town .
Hull Zero Three is a science fiction novel by American author Greg Bear .
The Yellow Silk ( ISBN 0 - 7869 - 3152 - 3 ) is a fantasy novel written by Don Bassingthwaite in 2004 .
Horrible Beginnings is an anthology of horror short stories edited by Steven H. Silver and Martin H. Greenberg , first published in paperback by DAW Books in March 2003 .
Betsy in Spite of Herself ( 1946 ) is the sixth volume in the Betsy - Tacy series by Maud Hart Lovelace .
Bokhandlaren som slutade bada ( The Bookseller Who Gave Up Bathing , 1937 ) is a novel by Fritiof Nilsson Piraten .
At the Gates of Darkness is a 2010 fantasy novel by Raymond E. Feist , the second book of his Demonwar Saga and the 26th book in his Riftwar Cycle .
The Buru Quartet is a literary tetralogy written by Indonesian author Pramoedya Ananta Toer .
Time for Elizabeth is a play written by Norman Krasna and Groucho Marx .
Sellevision ( 2000 ) a novel is the first work published by Augusten Burroughs , author of the best - selling books Running with Scissors , Dry , and Magical Thinking .
The Long Pursuit is a 1967 novel written by Australian author Jon Cleary about the escape of a group of survivors from the Battle of Singapore in World War II .
I Am Rosa Parks is a children 's book written by Brad Meltzer in the `` Ordinary People Change the World '' series .
Micah Clarke is an historical adventure novel by British author Arthur Conan Doyle , published in 1889 and set during the Monmouth Rebellion of 1685 in England .
Joseph and His Brothers ( Joseph und seine Brüder ) is a four - part novel by Thomas Mann , written over the course of 16 years .
The Stolen Throne is a fantasy novel written by Harry Turtledove and set in the Videssos universe .
The Prince of Venice Beach is a teenage novel by Blake Nelson .
Theory of the Absolute Individual ( Italian : Teoria Dell'individuo Assoluto ) is a work by Italian esoteric writer Julius Evola published in 1927 .
The Watch Below ( 1966 ) is a novel by science fiction author James White about a colony of humans stranded underwater in a sunken ship surviving due to air pockets .
The Gunmaker of Moscow is a serial novel by Sylvanus Cobb , Jr. first published in the New York Ledger starting on April 19 , 1856 .
Escape from Hell ! is a speculative fiction novella by Hal Duncan , strongly inspired by the movies Jacob 's Ladder and Escape from New York but also by the works of William Blake and John Milton .
Poverty is No Vice ( Bednost ne porok , Бедность не порок ) is a play by Alexander Ostrovsky , written in 1853 and published as a separate edition in the early 1854 .
Fantasy Twin is a collection of fantasy novels by L. Sprague de Camp and Stanley G. Weinbaum .
En dag i oktober ( eng : One day in October ) is a novel by Norwegian writer Sigurd Hoel , published in 1931 .
The Devil Finds Work is a book length essay by writer James Baldwin .
Data Tutashkhia ( Georgian : დათა თუთაშხია ) is a novel written by Chabua Amirejibi in 1975 .
Hang a Thousand Trees with Ribbons is a 1996 historical novel by Ann Rinaldi .
The Robot Scientist 's Daughter is a book of poetry that was written by Jeannine Hall Gailey and published by Mayapple Press in 2015 .
Midnight Predator is a vampire novel written by Amelia Atwater - Rhodes , published in 2002 when the author was 18 .
Baby with the Bathwater is a play by Christopher Durang about a boy named Daisy , his influences , and his eventual outcome .
`` Missile Gap '' is a 2006 English language science fiction novella , originally published in the anthology One Million A.D. by British author Charles Stross .
A Short History of Chinese Philosophy ( simplified Chinese : 中国哲学简史 ; traditional Chinese : 中國哲學簡史 ; pinyin : Zhōngguó zhéxué jiǎnshǐ ) is a book by Feng Youlan written in 1948 .
The Shoemaker is a play written by Susan Charlotte , first staged at the off - Broadway Acorn Theater on 24 July 2011 .
Shatter Me is a young adult dystopian thriller written by Tahereh Mafi , published on November 15 , 2011 .
Death Is My Trade ( French : La mort est mon métier ) is a 1952 French fictionalized biographical novel by Robert Merle .
Why I Am a Separatist is a political essay by Marcel Chaput , a militant for the independence of Quebec from Canada .
Capital and the Debt Trap is a research monograph by Claudia Sanchez Bajo and Bruno Roelants .
Marxism and Morality is a 1985 book by political and social theorist Steven Lukes ; it has been called a classic introduction .
The Second Generation is a collection of five novellas in the fantasy genre by Margaret Weis and Tracy Hickman .
Flash for Freedom ! is a 1971 novel by George MacDonald Fraser .
Genealogia Paulistana is a Brazilian historical - genealogical work written by Luís Gonzaga da Silva Leme , published in nine volumes between 1903 and 1905 .
Shards of a Broken Crown is a 1998 fantasy novel by Raymond E. Feist , the fourth and final book of his Serpentwar Saga and the twelfth book of his Riftwar cycle .
In the introduction to the Girls Gone By edition of The Marlows and the Traitor , Antonia Forest admits she never intended to write a series of books about the Marlows .
Five Go to Smuggler 's Top is the fourth book in the Famous Five series by the British author , Enid Blyton .
The Memoirs of Martinus Scriblerus is an incomplete satirical work ostensibly by the members of the Scriblerus Club but which was principally written by John Arbuthnot .
Sapphique is a young - adult fantasy and science fiction novel written by Catherine Fisher , first published in 2008 in the UK .
Empire of the Moghul is a series of historical fiction novels written by Alex Rutherford ( the pen name for Diana and Michael Preston ) .
The Consolation of Philosophy ( Latin : DE CONSOLATIONE PHILOSOPHIÆ ) is a work by the sixth - century philosopher Boethius that has been described as having had the single most important influence on the Christianity of the Middle Ages and early Renaissance and as the last great work of the Classical Period .
City of a Thousand Suns is a 1965 science fantasy novel by Samuel R. Delany , and is the final novel in the Fall of the Towers trilogy .
The Sad Detective ( Russian : Печальный Детектив ) is a story ( a short novel ) of notable Russian writer Viktor Astafyev .
The Black Spider is a novella by the Swiss writer Jeremias Gotthelf written in 1842 .
The Unbearable Lightness of Being a Prawn Cracker is a collection of Will Self 's Real Meals column for The New Statesman .
Business is business ( French : Les affaires sont les affaires ) is a French comedy in three acts , by the novelist and playwright Octave Mirbeau , performed in April 1903 on the stage of Comédie - Française , in Paris , and worldwide acclaimed , especially in Russia , Germany and United States .
Das Königsprojekt ( English : The Royal Project ) is a German - language science fiction novel by Carl Amery , published in 1974 .
Eve & Adam is a book by Michael Grant and Katherine Applegate published in 2012 by Feiwel and Friends .
The Dark Fields is a 2001 techno - thriller novel by Irish writer Alan Glynn .
`` And did those feet in ancient time '' is a short poem by William Blake from the preface to his epic Milton a Poem , one of a collection of writings known as the Prophetic Books .
The Sledding Hill is a 2005 post - modern metafictional novel by young adult writer Chris Crutcher .
A Void , translated from the original French La Disparition ( literally , `` The Disappearance '' ) , is a 300-page French lipogrammatic novel , written in 1969 by Georges Perec , entirely without using the letter e ( except for the author 's name ) , following Oulipo constraints .
A God Against the Gods is a 1976 historical novel by political novelist Allen Drury , which chronicles ancient Egyptian Pharaoh Akhenaten 's attempt to establish a new religion in Egypt .
James and the Giant Peach is a popular children 's novel written in 1961 by British author Roald Dahl .
`` The Duplicity of Hargraves '' is a short story by the American writer , William Sydney Porter , Pen name O. Henry .
A Firing Offense is a 1992 crime novel and the debut from author George Pelecanos .
Heavenly Breakfast is a 1979 autobigraphical novel by author , professor , and critic Samuel R. Delany .
The Sly Old Cat is a children 's book written and illustrated by Beatrix Potter in 1906 , and first published by Frederick Warne & Co. in 1971 , almost thirty years after her death .
A Dark Victory is a 1999 young - adult fantasy novel by Dave Luckett and is the last book in the Tenabran Trilogy .
The Admiral 's Daughter is a 1979 autobiography written by Victoria Fyodorova with Haskel Frankel .
Battledragon ( 1995 ) is a fantasy novel written by Christopher Rowley .
The Measure of the Magic is a fantasy novel by Terry Brooks released on August 23 , 2011 as the second of the two part Legends of Shannara series .
The Undying Land is a Lost race novel by William Gilmour .
The Pillars of Eternity is the tenth novel by the science fiction author Barrington J. Bayley .
The Void Trilogy is a science fiction series by British SF writer Peter F. Hamilton .
The Castle of Iron is the title of a fantasy novella by science fiction and fantasy authors L. Sprague de Camp and Fletcher Pratt , and to the novel into which it was later expanded by the same authors .
The Commentaries on the Laws of England are an influential 18th - century treatise on the common law of England by Sir William Blackstone , originally published by the Clarendon Press at Oxford , 1765 - -1769 .
The Death of Tintagiles ( French : La Mort de Tintagiles ) is an 1894 play by Belgian playwright Maurice Maeterlinck .
Things Hidden Since the Foundation of the World ( French : Des choses cachées depuis la fondation du monde ) is a 1978 book by philosopher of social science René Girard .
Fattypuffs and Thinifers ( ISBN 1903252075 ) is a 1941 translation of the French children 's book Patapoufs et Filifers originally written in 1930 by André Maurois .
Along Came a Dog is a children 's novel by Meindert DeJong , and Maurice Sendak .
Implied Spaces is a 2008 space opera novel by American author Walter Jon Williams .
Speak , Memory is an autobiographical memoir by writer Vladimir Nabokov .
Encounters with the Archdruid ( 1971 ) is a narrative nonfiction book by author John McPhee .
The Alchemist 's Question is a novella by British fantasy and science fiction writer Michael Moorcock .
Shutter Island is a best - selling novel by Dennis Lehane , published by Harper Collins in April 2003 .
The Last Dragonlord is the first in a series of books written by Joanne Bertin .
O Primo Basílio ( `` Cousin Bazilio '' ) is one of the most highly regarded realist novels of the Portuguese author José Maria de Eça de Queiroz , also known under the modernized spelling Eça de Queirós .
Epistolae familiares is the title of a collection of letters of Petrarch which he edited during his lifetime .
Landscape of Farewell is a 2007 novel by the Australian author Alex Miller .
Liberia ; or , Mr. Peyton 's Experiments is an 1853 novel by Sarah Josepha Hale , the author of the nursery rhyme `` Mary Had a Little Lamb '' , who wrote the novel under the name of Sara J. Hale .
How the Steel Was Tempered ( Russian : Как закалялась сталь , Kak zakalyalas ' stal ' ) is a socialist realist novel written by Nikolai Ostrovsky ( 1904 - -1936 ) .
`` The Man That Was Used Up '' , sometimes subtitled `` A Tale of the Late Bugaboo and Kickapoo Campaign '' , is a short story and satire by Edgar Allan Poe .
De Oratore ( On the Orator ; not to be confused with Orator ) is a dialogue written by Cicero in 55 BCE .
`` A Colder War '' is an English - language , alternate history novelette by Charles Stross written c. 1997 .
Counterexamples in Topology ( 1970 , 2nd ed . 1978 ) is a book on mathematics by topologists Lynn Steen and J. Arthur Seebach , Jr. In the process of working on problems like the metrization problem , topologists ( including Steen and Seebach ) have defined a wide variety of topological properties .
The Wasps ( Greek : Σφῆκες Sphēkes ) is the fourth in chronological order of the eleven surviving plays by Aristophanes , the master of an ancient genre of drama called ' Old Comedy ' .
Hart 's Hope ( 1983 ) is a fantasy novel by Orson Scott Card , written in second person .
Flying Saucers from Outer Space ( Holt , 1953 ) is a non - fiction book by Donald Keyhoe about unidentified flying objects , aka UFO .
The Fortified Castle ( Arabic : القلعة الحصينة‎ Al - Qala - ah Al - Hasinah ) is Saddam Hussein 's third of four novels .
Al - Kamal fi Asma ' al - Rijal ( Arabic : الكمال في أسماء الرجال‎ ) is a collection of biographies of hadith narrators within the Islamic discipline of biographical evaluation by the 12th - century Islamic scholar Abd al - Ghani al - Maqdisi .
13 Alabama Ghosts and Jeffrey is a book first published in 1969 by folklorist Kathryn Tucker Windham and Margaret Gillis Figh .
Voyages de l'autre côté is a novel written in French by French Nobel laureate writer J. M. G. Le Clézio .
Winter in Eden is a 1986 science fiction novel by American author Harry Harrison , the second in the Eden series .
First Meetings ( 2002 ) is a collection of Orson Scott Card 's short stories from the Ender 's Game series .
Oh No It Is n't ! is a novel published in 1997 by Paul Cornell from the Virgin New Adventures featuring the fictional archaeologist Bernice Summerfield .
Just Give Me a Cool Drink of Water ' fore I Diiie ( 1971 ) is the first collection of poems by African - American writer and poet , Maya Angelou .
Hortus Kewensis , or a Catalogue of the Plants Cultivated in the Royal Botanic Garden at Kew by William Aiton was a 1789 catalogue of all the plant species then in cultivation at the Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew , which constituted the vast majority of plant species in cultivation in all of England .
Labyrinth of Reflections is the first novel in the Labyrinth trilogy of cyberpunk novels written by Russian science fiction writer Sergey Lukyanenko .
The Years of Rice and Salt is an alternate history novel written by science fiction author Kim Stanley Robinson and published in 2002 .
Night World is a series of ten ( with the tenth as yet unpublished ) young - adult fantasy novels by American author L. J. Smith .
The Terrorists was unfinished at the time of Per Wahlöö 's death in June 1975 ; the manuscript was completed by Maj Sjöwall alone .
The Fish Can Sing ( Icelandic : Brekkukotsannáll ) is a 1957 novel by Icelandic author Halldór Laxness , who was awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1955 .
Mounting Fears is the seventh novel in the Will Lee series by Stuart Woods .
Mera Pakistani Safarnama is a Punjabi travelogue by actor - writer Balraj Sahni .
The Defence of the Seven Sacraments ( in Latin , Assertio Septem Sacramentorum ) is a theological treatise from 1521 , officially written by King Henry VIII of England , though more likely by John Fisher .
Dancing Lessons for the Advanced in Age ( Czech : Taneční hodiny pro starší a pokročilé ) is a 1964 novel by the Czechoslovak writer Bohumil Hrabal .
Time in Advance ( no ISBN ) is a collection of four short stories by science fiction writer William Tenn ( a pseudonym for the sci - fi work of Philip Klass ) .
Gates of Fire is a 1998 historical fiction novel by Steven Pressfield that recounts the Battle of Thermopylae through Xeones , a helot slave / squire , and one of only three Greek survivors of the battle .
Traitor 's Blood is a novel by Reginald Hill , the author best known for his Dalziel and Pascoe series of crime novels .
Reservoir Pups ( also known as Running with the Reservoir Pups ) is the first novel of the Eddie & the Gang with No Name trilogy by Northern Irish author , Colin Bateman , published on 13 November 2003 through Hodder Children 's Books .
Uncle Target is a third person narrative novel by English author Gavin Lyall , first published in 1988 , and the fourth and last in his series of novels with the character `` Harry Maxim '' as the protagonist .
Elmer the Patchwork Elephant is a children 's picture book series by the British author David McKee .
Pierre Tombal is a Belgian gag cartoon strip , drawn by Marc Hardy and with text by Raoul Cauvin , about a mortician and the dead people at his cemetery .
Wisconsin Murders is a collection of true crime accounts written by author August Derleth .
The Naughtiest Girl Keeps a Secret ( 1999 ) is the first of a continuation of Enid Blyton 's The Naughtiest Girl series by Anne Digby .
Body Awareness is a one - act play by Annie Baker .
Victor Mishalow was awarded the title of Merited Artist of Ukraine by Ukrainian president Leonid Kuchma in October , 1999 .
Major Matthew Fontaine Maury Meiklejohn VC ( 27 November 1870 -- 4 July 1913 ) was a British recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Albéric Clément ( c. 1165 -- 1191 ) was the first Marshal of France under Philip Augustus , appointed to that position in 1185 .
Prince Michał Fryderyk Czartoryski ( 1696 - 1775 ) was a Polish nobleman , the Duke of Klewań and Żuków , magnate , and Knight of the Order of the White Eagle ( from 1726 ) .
Sergei Vasilyev was granted the honorary title of People 's Artist of the USSR in 1948 ; and received ( with Georgi Vasilyev ) two Stalin Prizes in 1941 and 1942 .
In 1996 , The Awful Truth was selected for preservation in the United States National Film Registry , having been deemed `` culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant '' .
Ugo de Carolis ( born 1887 and killed in action 12 December 1941 ) was a Brigadier - General and commander of the 52 Motorised Division Torino on the eastern front during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Luz Marina Zuluaga Zuluaga ( Spanish pronunciation : ( suˈlwaɣa ) ; October 31 , 1938 -- December 2 , 2015 ) was a Colombian beauty queen who won Miss Universe 1958 .
Dancer in the Dark premiered at the 2000 Cannes Film Festival to standing ovations and controversy , but was nonetheless awarded the Palme d'Or , along with the Best Actress award for Björk .
Video recording of lecture ( in Latvian ) can be accessed via daugavasvanagi.ca Uldis Ģērmanis was elected a member of the Latvian Academy of Sciences in 1992 and awarded the Order of the Three Stars in 1995 .
Ben Quilty ( born 1973 in Sydney ) is an Australian artist who won the 2014 Prudential Eye Award , 2011 Archibald Prize and 2009 Doug Moran National Portrait Prize .
George Waller VC ( June 1827 -- 10 January 1877 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
In 2008 , So 's Your Old Man was added to the United States National Film Registry .
Rico Roman ( born February 4 , 1981 ) is an American gold medal sledge hockey player and Purple Heart recipient from Portland , Oregon who competed in 2014 Winter Paralympics in Sochi , Russia .
Ehrenfried - Oskar Boege ( 11 November 1889 -- 31 December 1965 ) was a German general who held several Corps level commands during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
On July 23 , 2003 , John Wooden received the Presidential Medal of Freedom , the nation 's highest civilian honor .
In 2006 , the Adva Center was the recipient of the Emil Grunzweig Human Rights Award , bestowed by the Association for Civil Rights in Israel .
For it Temporary Lt George Butterworth , aged 31 , was awarded the Military Cross , gazetted 25 August 1916 , although he did not live to receive it .
Michael Ancher received the Eckersberg Medal in 1889 and in 1894 the Order of the Dannebrog .
Foundation 's Edge won the Hugo Award for Best Novel in 1983 , and was nominated for the Nebula Award for Best Novel in 1982 .
John Curro was appointed a Member of the Order of the British Empire in 1981 , and a Member of the Order of Australia in 1995 .
Philip Lucas GM ( 1902 - -1981 ) was an English aviator and test pilot who was awarded the George Medal for his courage and skill landing a damaged Hawker Typhoon prototype .
Ernest Albert Garlington ( February 20 , 1853 -- October 16 , 1934 ) was a United States Army general who received the Medal of Honor during the Indian Wars .
His film music for the Line was awarded with Buddyprisen in 1960 , and he led his own Mikkel Flagstad Quintet including Atle Hammer ( trumpet ) , Kjell Karlsen ( piano ) , Erik Amundsen ( bass ) and Ole Jacob Hansen ( drums ) , while he took dentist education .
Akshayraj Kore ( born 1 September 1988 ) , is an Indian chess player and a Grandmaster .
Keith Looby ( born 1940 in Sydney , Australia ) , is an Australian artist who won the Archibald Prize in 1984 with a portrait of Max Gillies .
Percy Edward Kent ( 18 March 1913 - 9 July 1986 ) PhD , DSc , LLD , ScD , FGS , FRS was a British geologist who won the Royal Medal in 1971 .
Michael Moss was awarded the Pulitzer Prize for Explanatory Reporting in 2010 , and was a finalist for the prize in 2006 and 1999 .
In the 1968 Queen 's Birthday Honours , Stefan Haag was appointed an Officer of the Order of the British Empire for his development of the performing arts .
Zhu Chen ( simplified Chinese : 诸宸 ; traditional Chinese : 諸宸 ; pinyin : Zhū Chén ; born March 16 , 1976 in Wenzhou , Zhejiang ) is a Qatari chess Grandmaster .
Nadine Gordimer ( 20 November 1923 -- 13 July 2014 ) was a South African writer , political activist and recipient of the 1991 Nobel Prize in Literature .
Othmar Kreuzinger ( 9 September 1919 -- 13 September 1944 ) was a Hauptmann of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Simon Sez is a 1999 action comedy film starring Dennis Rodman , Dane Cook , and John Pinette .
Stephanie 's Image is a 2009 American drama film directed by Janis DeLucia Allen , written by JP Allen and featuring Melissa Leo in the title role .
The Snake Woman is a low budget 1961 British horror film directed by Sidney J. Furie and starring Susan Travers , John McCarthy .
Demon Knight is a feature - length film presented by the HBO series Tales from the Crypt , and features scenes with the Crypt Keeper ( voiced by John Kassir , as in the series ) at the beginning and end of the film .

Armless is a 2010 comedy film directed by Habib Azar and written by Kyle Jarrow , starring Daniel London , Janel Moloney , Matt Walton , Zoe Lister - Jones and Laurie Kennedy .
Imitation General is a 1958 CinemaScope war comedy film starring Glenn Ford , Red Buttons and Taina Elg .
Once Upon a Crime is a 1992 ensemble comedy film starring Richard Lewis , John Candy , James Belushi , Cybill Shepherd , Sean Young and Ornella Muti .
Under the Yum Yum Tree is a 1963 comedy movie that stars Jack Lemmon , Carol Lynley , Dean Jones , and Edie Adams , with supporting roles by Imogene Coca and Paul Lynde .
The Home at Hong Kong is a 1983 Hong Kong drama film directed by King Hoi Lam and starring Andy Lau .
Gnana Soundari is a 1948 Indian Tamil historical fiction film written , produced and directed by duo F. Nagoor and Joseph Thalaith Jr. The film stars T. R. Mahalingam , M. V. Rajamma in lead roles with D. Balasubramaniam , Sivabhagyam , Lalitha and Padmini playing supporting roles .
Crucible of Terror is a 1971 British horror film directed by Ted Hooker and starring Mike Raven , Mary Maude and James Bolam .
Brother Orchid is a 1940 American crime / comedy film directed by Lloyd Bacon and starring Edward G. Robinson , Ann Sothern and Humphrey Bogart , with featured performances by Donald Crisp , Ralph Bellamy and Allen Jenkins .
Absence of Malice is a 1981 American drama film starring Paul Newman , Sally Field , and Bob Balaban , directed by Sydney Pollack .
A.F.R.I.K.A. ( Hangul : 아프리카 ; RR : Apeurika ) is a 2002 South Korean film in the action comedy genre , directed by Shin Seung - soo and starring Lee Yo - won , Kim Min - sun , Lee Young - jin and Jo Eun - ji .
True Legend is a 2010 Chinese martial arts film directed by Yuen Woo - ping , starring Vincent Zhao , Zhou Xun , Jay Chou , Michelle Yeoh , Andy On , David Carradine , Guo Xiaodong , Feng Xiaogang , Cung Le , Gordon Liu , Bryan Leung and Jacky Heung .
Toofan Aur Deeya is a 1956 Bollywood film directed by Prabhat Kumar and starring Satish Vyas , Nanda , Rajendra Kumar , Vatsala Deshmukh , Shanta Kumari , Krishna Kumar , Keshavrao Date and Ulhas .
Gidget Goes Hawaiian is a 1961 musical romantic comedy film starring Deborah Walley and James Darren .
Man in a Hurry ( French : L'Homme pressé , Italian : L'ultimo giorno d'amore , released in UK as The Hurried Man ) is a 1977 French - Italian drama film directed by Édouard Molinaro and starring Alain Delon and Mireille Darc .
Death on the Diamond is a 1934 mystery film starring Robert Young as a baseball player who has to figure out who is trying to murder the members of his team , the Saint Louis Cardinals .
Tre må man være is a 1959 Danish family film directed by Sven Methling and starring Poul Reichhardt .
The Fighter is a 2010 American biographical sports drama film directed by David O. Russell , and starring Mark Wahlberg , Christian Bale , Amy Adams and Melissa Leo .
Daughter of Shanghai is a 1937 American motion picture directed by Robert Florey , written by Gladys Unger and Garnett Weston , and starring Anna May Wong and Philip Ahn .

The STEN ( or Sten gun ) was a family of British submachine guns chambered in 9×19 mm and used extensively by British and Commonwealth forces throughout World War II and the Korean War .

Walter Zellot ( 6 October 1920 -- 10 September 1942 ) was a World War II fighter ace from Germany .
Marina Ginestà i Coloma ( 29 January 1919 -- 6 January 2014 ) was a French veteran of the Spanish Civil War , who was a member of the Unified Socialist Youth .
Hans Drexel ( 12 November 1919 -- 12 April 1962 ) was a Hauptsturmführer ( Captain ) in the Waffen - SS during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .

HD 8535 b ( also known as HIP 6511 b ) is an extrasolar planet which orbits the G - type main sequence star HD 8535 , located approximately 171 light years away in the constellation Phoenix .

Fisher Bastion ( 78 ° 21′S 162 ° 31′E ) is a high rectangular massif , 2,650 metres ( 8,700 ft ) high , between the upper reaches of Potter Glacier and Foster Glacier , 4.5 nautical miles ( 8 km ) southeast of Mount Huggins in the Royal Society Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Arrival Heights are clifflike heights which extend in a north - east -- south - west direction along the west side of Hut Point Peninsula , just north of Hut Point in Ross Island , Antarctica .
Between Russian Hill and North Beach is San Francisco 's Chinatown , the oldest Chinatown in North America .
Mount Goossens ( 71 ° 19′S 35 ° 44′E ) is a largely bare rock massif , 2,200 metres ( 7,200 ft ) high , standing next south of Mount Pierre in the Queen Fabiola Mountains of Antarctica .
Sotos Point is a glaciated point projecting 180 m into the southeast part of Discovery Bay , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and forming the east side of the entrance to Montecinos Cove ( 62 ° 29′57``S 59 ° 40′59''W ) .
Edinburgh , the country 's capital and second - largest city , was the hub of the Scottish Enlightenment of the 18th century , which transformed Scotland into one of the commercial , intellectual , and industrial powerhouses of Europe .
Heiser Ridge ( 83 ° 50′S 57 ° 9′W ) is a narrow rock ridge , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , midway between the West Prongs and Hudson Ridge in the Neptune Range of the Pensacola Mountains in Antarctica .
Miller Butte ( 72 ° 42′S 160 ° 15′E ) is a large rock butte located 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southeast of Roberts Butte in the Outback Nunataks of Antarctica .
Aim Rocks is a group of rocks lying east of Cape Timblón in the middle of Morton Strait in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Krakken Hill ( 71 ° 57′S 26 ° 14′E ) is a rocky hill standing in Byrdbreen , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) east of Bautaen Peak in the Sør Rondane Mountains of Antarctica .
Neptune Glacier ( 71 ° 44′S 68 ° 17′W ) is a glacier on the east coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica , 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long and 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) wide , flowing east into George VI Sound and the George VI Ice Shelf to the south of Triton Point .
Bacho Kiro Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Бачо Киро , `` Vrah Bacho Kiro '' \'vr&h ' ba - cho ' ki - ro\ ) is the rocky , partly ice - free peak rising to 1500 m between Woodbury Glacier and Montgolfier Glacier on Danco Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Hageman Peak ( 71 ° 43′S 70 ° 48′W ) is a montane landform pinnacle rising to about 940 metres ( 3,100 ft ) at the northwest end of the Staccato Peaks in southern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
New Mountain is a mountain in Antarctica .
Cape Whitson , is a headland on the south coast of Laurie Island , the easternmost and second largest of the South Orkney Islands of Antarctica .
Gamble Glacier ( 81 ° 6′S 156 ° 45′E ) is a glacier flowing northwest from Chapman Snowfield , and located between Green Nunatak at the southwest and Keating Massif at the northeast , in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
The Lorn Rocks ( 65 ° 31′S 64 ° 56′W ) are a group of rocks lying 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) west of the north end of Lahille Island , in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica .
Woodgyer Peak ( 81 ° 13′S 156 ° 20′E ) is a peak above 2000 m in the Wallabies Nunataks , west of the Churchill Mountains in Antarctica .
The Furman Bluffs ( 74 ° 6′S 113 ° 53′W ) are a line of steep ice bluffs that form the southeast side of Philbin Inlet on Martin Peninsula , Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Napier Peak is the partly ice - free peak rising to 380 m on Hurd Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Tatul Island ( Bulgarian : остров Татул , `` Ostrov Tatul '' \'os - trov ta-'tul\ ) is a triangular ice - free island off the north coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Dotson Ice Shelf is an ice shelf about 30 miles ( 50 km ) wide between Martin Peninsula and Bear Peninsula on the coast of Marie Byrd Land in Antarctica .
Brown Range or Sørtindane Peaks is a group of seven peaks in Framnes Mountains about 4 km south of Mount Twintop in Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .
Ant Hill ( 78 ° 47′S 161 ° 27′E ) is a hill on Antarctica , 1,310 metres ( 4,300 ft ) high , rising steeply on the west side of the Skelton Glacier between Ant Hill Glacier and Dilemma Glacier .
Stoker Island is a rocky island lying off the north coast of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Drong Hill ( Bulgarian : хълм Дронг , `` Halm Drong '' \'h&lm ' drong\ ) is the double rocky hill rising to 179 m in the northwest extremity of Dospey Heights on Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Havstein Island is a rocky island , 6 km ( 3 nmi ) long and 4 km ( 2 nmi ) wide , situated 3 km ( 1.5 nmi ) north of Law Promontory and 2 km ( 1 nmi ) east of Broka Island , in Antarctica .
Gadarene Lake ( 71 ° 24′S 67 ° 35′W ) is a meltwater lake 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) long in the ice shelf of George VI Sound , lying below Swine Hill with its eastern shore bounding the exposed rocks of the west coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Stackpole Rocks is a group of rocks , the largest of them linked by a spit to the east extremity of South Beaches in Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Torgersen Island is a small rocky island lying just east of Litchfield Island in the entrance to Arthur Harbour , off the south - west coast of Anvers Island in the Palmer Archipelago of Antarctica .
Landing Bluff is a rock mass in Antarctica with a steep slope on the eastern side , with several small outcrops just to the south - west .
Patriot Hills ( 80 ° 20′S 81 ° 25′W ) is a line of rock hills 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , located 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of the north end of Independence Hills in Horseshoe Valley , Heritage Range , Western Antarctica .
The Lajarte Islands ( 64 ° 14′S 63 ° 24′W ) are a group of islands fringing the north coast of Anvers Island , close west of Cape Grönland and 1.5 km east - northeast of Lapteva Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Bogdan Ridge ( Rid Bogdan \'rid ' bog - dan\ ) is a conspicuous rocky ridge of elevation 440 m forming the northeast extremity of Breznik Heights , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Hourihan Glacier ( 80 ° 8′S 158 ° 45′E ) is a glacier draining the south slopes of Ward Tower in the Britannia Range , Antarctica , and flowing southeast to Merrick Glacier .
Cape Goldie ( 82 ° 38′S 165 ° 54′E ) is a cape at the south side of the mouth of Robb Glacier , overlooking the Ross Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
Cape Goodenough ( 66 ° 16′S 126 ° 10′E ) is an ice - covered cape marking the west side of the entrance to Porpoise Bay and forming the northernmost projection of Norths Highland in Antarctica .
Hudson Ridge ( 83 ° 47′S 56 ° 39′W ) is a narrow rock ridge 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , lying 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) north of Heiser Ridge in the Neptune Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Intuition Peak ( Vrah Intuitsiya \'vr&h in - tu-'i - tsi - ya\ ) is a sharp Antarctic peak of elevation 780 m in Levski Ridge , Tangra Mountains on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount Lunde ( 66 ° 58′S 50 ° 28′E ) is a mountain ridge close south of Mount Gleadell , in the western part of the Tula Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
MacAlpine Hills ( 84 ° 13′S 160 ° 30′E ) are a chain of mainly ice - free , bluff - type hills in Antarctica , extending from Mount Achernar southwestwards along the south side of Law Glacier , to Sylwester Glacier .
The Hobbs Islands are a group of islands 19 kilometres ( 10 nmi ) northeast of William Scoresby Bay , Antarctica .
Oates Land is a wedge - shaped segment of East Antarctica stretching along and inland from the Oates Coast .
Radomir Knoll ( Radomirska Mogila \'ra - do - mir - ska mo-'gi - la\ ) rises to approximately 300 m in Prespa Glacier , eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Cerro Torre is one of the mountains of the Southern Patagonian Ice Field in South America .
Andersson Peak ( 64 ° 52′S 61 ° 2′W ) is an ice - capped peak , 1,230 metres ( 4,040 ft ) high , with rocky exposures on its east side , lying 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) north of Cape Fairweather on the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Varshets Saddle ( Bulgarian : седловина Вършец , `` Sedlovina Varshets '' \se - dlo - vi-'na v&r-'shets\ ) is a saddle of elevation 1430 m in Imeon Range on Smith Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica bounded by Antim Peak to the south - southwest and Slatina Peak to the east .
The Nakaya Islands are a small group of islands in Crystal Sound , about 18 km northeast of Cape Rey , Graham Land in Antarctica .
The Alligator Eyes ( 81 ° 38′S 160 ° 55′E ) are two adjacent nunataks that rise to over 600 metres ( 2,000 ft ) on the east side of Dickey Glacier in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
Hayes Peak is a conical peak in Antarctica , that reaches 340 metres ( 1,120 ft ) high , rising through the ice slopes 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south of Cape Bruce and Oom Bay .
The Marø Cliffs ( 79 ° 4′S 28 ° 30′W ) are prominent rock cliffs standing southwest of Jeffries Glacier in the Theron Mountains of Antarctica .
Also located on the Bürgenstock is Europe 's tallest outdoor lift : the Hammetschwand Lift connects the beautiful scenic cliff path with the Hammetschwand vantage point , from where spectacular views of Lake Lucerne and the surrounding mountains are to be had .
The Glover Hills ( 76 ° 41′S 161 ° 40′E ) are prominent hills separating Atka Glacier and Baxter Glacier in the Convoy Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Gurney Point ( 71 ° 0′S 67 ° 27′W ) is a small rocky mass overlooking George VI Sound , rising to 610 metres ( 2,000 ft ) and marking the western extremity of the rock ridge separating Bertram Glacier and Ryder Glacier on the west coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Gardner Inlet ( 74 ° 58′S 62 ° 52′W ) is a large , ice - filled inlet at the southwest side of Bowman Peninsula , on the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Frostlendet Valley is an ice - filled valley , about 15 miles ( 24 km ) long , draining northeastward along the south side of Hogfonna Mountain , in the Borg Massif of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Kainan Bay is an iceport which indents the front of the Ross Ice Shelf about 37 nautical miles ( 70 km ) northeast of the northwestern end of Roosevelt Island , Antarctica .
The Hall Nunataks ( 70 ° 48′S 66 ° 45′E ) are a group of four nunataks about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) east - southeast of Mount Bunt in the Aramis Range of the Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .
Rayko Nunatak ( Bulgarian : Райков нунатак , `` Raykov Nunatak '' \'ray - kov ' nu - na - tak\ ) is the rocky hill rising to 750 m in the northeast foothills of Detroit Plateau on southern Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica , surmounting Diplock Glacier to the north and Zavera Snowfield to the southeast .
West Aisle Ridge ( 78 ° 20′S 163 ° 12′E ) in Antarctica is a named from the position of the ridge in a group of three ridges in relation to The Stage .

The Allied Kommandatura , or often just Kommandatura , also known as the Alliierte Kommandantur in German , was the governing body for the city of Berlin following Germany 's defeat in World War II . The victorious allied powers established control of post - war Germany and other territories via shared Military Government councils , including for Berlin .

Ivan Babaryka ( Ukrainian : Іван Бабарика ; born 11 November 1982 ) is a Ukrainian long distance runner who specialises in the marathon .
Arthur Siskind ( born 11 October 1938 ) is a lawyer and businessperson .
Dr. Kunwar Bechain ( born 1 July 1942 ) is a Hindi poet of India .
Jarlesson Inácio Júnior ( born 22 February 1990 ) , commonly known as Juninho Potiguar is a Brazilian footballer , who plays for Al Shabab Dubai .
Klaus - Jürgen Deuser ( born 28 May 1962 ) is a German presenter and comedian .
Yigal Carmon ( Hebrew יגאל כרמון ) ( born 1946 ) is the president and cofounder of the Middle East Media Research Institute ( MEMRI ) , an organization which monitors and translates Arabic and Persian publications ; radio and TV broadcasts ; and religious sermons into many languages and circulates them over the Internet .
Spike Heatley ( born 17 February 1933 ) is a British jazz bassist .
Kim Joo - won ( Hangul , 김주원 ; born 1978 ) is a South Korean prima ballerina who has danced for 15 years with the Korean National Ballet ( KNB ) .
Mattia Notari ( born 20 May 1979 ) is an Italian football player who plays as a centre back .
Wendy Padbury ( born 7 December 1947 ) is a British actress who appeared in a number of popular television series , and is probably best remembered as a companion to Doctor Who during the Patrick Troughton era .
Morten P. Meldal ( born 1954 in Denmark ) is a Danish chemist .
Abraham Raimbach ( 16 February 1776 in London -- 17 January 1843 ) , was an English line - engraver of Swiss descent .
Simone Moro ( born 27 October 1967 ) is an Italian alpinist .
Farid Esack ( born 1959 in Wynberg , Cape Town ) is a South African Muslim scholar , writer , and political activist known for his opposition to apartheid , his appointment by Nelson Mandela as a gender equity commissioner , and his work for inter - religious dialogue .
Marius Goring , CBE ( 23 May 1912 -- 30 September 1998 ) was an English stage and film actor .
Ladislav Prášil ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈlaɟɪslaf ˈpraːʃɪl ) ) ( born 17 May 1990 ) is a Czech shot putter .
Mark Schweizer ( born 1956 ) is an American musician , composer , writer , and music professor .
Kyros Vassaras ( born 1 February 1966 ) is a Greek former professional football referee .
Tom Naegels ( born 14 October 1975 , Antwerp ) is a Belgian author and journalist .
Bernard Holland ( born 1933 ) is an American music critic .
Steven Dietz ( born 23 June 1958 , Denver , Colorado ) is an American playwright whose thirty - plus plays have been widely produced in the U.S. and internationally .
Kwon Jip ( Hangul : 권집 ; born 13 February 1984 ) is a South Korean footballer .
Aleksandar Boljević ( Montenegrin Cyrillic : Александар Бољевић ; born 12 December 1995 ) is a Montenegrin footballer who plays as a winger for Eredivisie side PSV .
Piers Faccini ( born Piers Damian G. Faccini ; 1970 ) is an English singer , painter and songwriter .
Munir Ahmad Khan ( Urdu : منير احمد خان‎ ; b. 20 May 1926 -- 22 April 1999 ; NI HI ) , was a Pakistani nuclear engineer and a nuclear physicist , who served as the chairman of the Pakistan Atomic Energy Commission ( PAEC ) from 1972 to 1991 .
Joseph Greenhill ( 1704 - -1788 ) was an English theological writer .
Alfredo Eduardo Barreto de Freitas Noronha , better known as Noronha ( 25 September 1918 -- 27 July 2003 ) , was a Brazilian football player .
Pura Belpré ( 1899 - -1982 ) was the first Puerto Rican librarian in New York City .
Andrew Leete Stone ( b. Nov. 25 , 1815 ; d. Jan. 16 , 1892 ) was an author , Civil War chaplain and pastor of Park Street Church in Boston , Massachusetts , USA .
Leo Willis ( 5 January 1890 -- 10 April 1952 ) was an American actor who began his career in the silent era .
Enni Ben'en ( 圓爾辯圓 ; Chinese Yuan'er Bianyuan ; 1202 - -1280 ) was a Japanese Buddhist monk .
Harriet Hallowell ( 1873 - -1943 ) was an expatriate American artist who lived in France for fifty years .
James Desmond Buckle ( 29 March 1910 -- 25 October 1964 ) was a political activist and journalist born in the British colony of the Gold Coast ( present - day Ghana ) .
James Tilghman ( 1716 - -1793 ) was a prominent lawyer and public servant in colonial Maryland and Pennsylvania .
Clemente Domínguez y Gómez ( 23 May 1946 -- 22 March 2005 ) was a self - proclaimed successor of Pope Paul VI , and was recognised as Pope Gregory XVII by supporters of the Palmarian Catholic Church breakway movement in 1978 .
Hans von Koessler ( 1 January 1853 -- 23 May 1926 ) was a German composer , conductor and music teacher .
John M. Darby ( September 3 or September 27 , 1804 -- September 18 , 1877 ) was an American botanist , chemist , and academic .
Lorine Livington Pruette ( 1896 - -1977 ) was an American feminist , psychologist , and writer , whose ideas on women , marriage , the family , and women 's role in society are often considered ahead of her time .
Michel Cartry ( 1931 - -2008 ) was a French Africanist and anthropologist of religion .
Boleslaus Goral or Bolesław Góral ( March 12 , 1876 -- 1960 ) was a Polish - American priest , professor , and newspaper editor .
Peter Buchan ( 1790 -- 19 September 1854 ) , Scottish was a Scottish editor , publisher , and collector of ballads and folktales .
Karl Edvard Diriks ( 9 January 1855 -- 17 March 1930 ) was a Norwegian painter who resided in France between 1899 and 1921 .
Pierre Granier ( 1655 -- 1715 ) was a proficient but minor French sculptor , trained in the excellent atelier of François Girardon who produced a generation of highly competent sculptors for the Bâtiments du Roi .
Richard Beeching , Baron Beeching ( 21 April 1913 -- 23 March 1985 ) , commonly known as Dr Beeching , was chairman of British Railways and a physicist and engineer .
Ramon Riu i Cabanes ( 17 June 1852 -- 27 December 1901 ) was Bishop of Urgell and ex officio Co - Prince of Andorra in 1901 .
Jack Witikka ( 20 December 1916 -- 28 January 2002 ; surname until 1942 Jakobsson ) was a Finnish film director and screenwriter .
Jarosław of Bogoria and Skotniki ( Polish : Jarosław z Bogorii i Skotnik ) ( ca . 1276 -- 17 September 1376 ) was a Polish nobleman and bishop , member of the Bogoriowie family of the Bogorya Coat of Arms .
Gaston Salmon ( 5 March 1878 -- 30 April 1917 ) was a Belgian épée , foil , and sabre fencer .
Manjeshwar Ganapathi Rao Aigal ( 1881 - -1944 ) was a Historian and served as a Teacher in Bantwal , Dakshina Kannada .
Count Christian Karl Reinhard of Leiningen - Dachsburg - Falkenburg - Heidesheim ( 17 July 1695 , Mülheim an der Ruhr -- 17 November 1766 , Heidesheim ) was a German nobleman .
Mu'inud - Daulah , Mushirul - Mulk , Azamul - Umara , Arastu Jah , a man of Persian descent , was the diwan or the prime minister of Nizam Ali Khan ( Asaf Jah II ) of Hyderabad from 1778 until his death in 1804 .
Sydney Strickland Tully ( 1860 - 1911 ) was a Canadian academic painter .
Jørgen Aall ( 22 February 1771 -- 7 April 1833 ) was a Norwegian ship - owner and politician .
Colonel William Digges ( c1651- 24 July 1697 ) was a politician in Colonial Virginia and a councillor in Colonial Maryland in the late seventeenth and early eighteenth centuries .
Thomas Cartter Lupton ( 1899 - 1977 ) was an American heir and businessman .
Sir William Beddoe Rees , usually known simply as Beddoe Rees ( 1877 -- 12 May 1931 ) was a Welsh architect , industrialist and Liberal politician .
Jean - Noël Rey ( 23 December 1949 -- 16 January 2016 ) was a Swiss manager and politician of the Social Democratic Party .
Joseph Redfearn ( 13 May 1862 -- 14 January 1931 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played one match for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1890 against Surrey .
Sokolluzade Lala Mehmed Pasha ( died 21 June 1606 ) was a Bosnian Ottoman statesman .
Daniel Jonsson ( 1599 - -1663 ) was a soldier and commander of Dalregementet of the Swedish Empire .
Karl Sutter ( 10 May 1914 - -14 September 2003 ) was a German track and field athlete who competed in the pole vault .
José Jaime Pierluisi ( 12 June 1965 -- 7 June 1994 ) was an economic adviser to Puerto Rico Governor Pedro Rosselló from 1993 until his death during a carjacking on June 7 , 1994 .
G. Owen Bonawit ( 1891 - -1971 ) was an artist whose studio created thousands of pieces of stained glass for Yale , Duke , Northwestern , and Southeast Missouri State universities ;
Rodrigo Asturias Amado ( 30 October 1939 -- 15 June 2005 ) was a Guatemalan guerrilla leader and politician .
Sir Nicholas Bayard Dill ( 28 December 1905 -- 10 September 1993 ) , known as Bayard Dill , was a prominent Bermudian politician , lawyer and military officer .
Prince Pashaura Singh ( 1821 -- 11 September 1845 ) ( also Peshawara Singh ) was one of the sons of Maharaja Ranjit Singh .
Ulick Burke , 3rd Earl of Clanricarde , Irish peer , died 1601 .
Li Changyan ( 李昌言 ) ( d. 884 ) was a warlord of the late Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who controlled Fengxiang Circuit ( 鳳翔 , headquartered in modern Baoji , Shaanxi ) from 881 to 884 as its military governor ( Jiedushi ) after overthrowing his predecessor , the former chancellor Zheng Tian .
Rafael Batlle Pacheco ( 1888 , Montevideo - 1960 ) was a Uruguayan journalist .
Willem van Haecht ( 1593 -- 12 July 1637 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter best known for his gallery pictures and the son of the landscape painter Tobias Verhaecht .
Alexander Walker Scott ( 10 November 1800 -- 1 November 1883 ) was an Australian entomologist mainly interested in butterflies .
James Primadicci ( early 15th century , Bologna , Signoria of Bologna ( Italy ) -- 1460 , Bologna ) was a Papal diplomat who was particularly charged with sensitive attempts to bring Eastern churches back into communion with Rome .
Gianfranco Ferré ( Italian pronunciation : ( dʒamˈfraŋko ferˈre ) ) ( 15 August 1944 -- 17 June 2007 ) was a fashion designer also known as `` the architect of fashion '' for his background and his original attitude toward creating fashion design .
Ghulam Mohammed Sadiq ( 1912 -- 1971 ) was the Prime Minister of Jammu and Kashmir from 1964 to 1965 , when the position was abolished .
Isabella of England ( 1214 -- 1 December 1241 ) , was Holy Roman Empress , Queen of the Germans , and Queen consort of Sicily .
Stefan Nemanjić ( Serbian : Стефан Немањић , pronounced ( stêfaːn němaɲitɕ ) ) or Stefan the First - Crowned ( Стефан Првовенчани/Stefan Prvovenčani , IPA : ( stêfaːn prʋoʋěntʃaːniː ) ; around 1165 -- 24 September 1228 ) was Grand Prince of Serbia from 1196 , and the King of Serbia from 1217 until his death in 1228 .
M. Asaduzzaman ( Bengali : অধ্যাপক আসাদুজ্জামান ; c. 1948 -- 28 March 2008 ) was a professor in the Public Administration Department of Dhaka University and chairman of the University Grants Commission of Bangladesh ( UGC ) .
Jalal al - Din Mahmud ( died 1352 ) was the Mihrabanid malik of Sistan from 1350 until his death .
John de Vere , 7th Earl of Oxford ( c. 12 March 1312 -- 24 January 1360 ) was the nephew and heir of Robert de Vere , 6th Earl of Oxford who succeeded as Earl of Oxford in 1331 , after his uncle died without issue .
Ole Andreas Lindeman ( 17 January 1769 -- 26 February 1857 ) was a Norwegian musician , organist , composer and music educator .
William Briton or Breton ( died 1356 ) was a Breton Franciscan theologian .
Robert Bruce Tague ( 1912 - 1985 ) was an American modernist architect and abstract artist who lived in Chicago , Illinois .
Robert Alves ( 1745 - -1794 ) , was a Scottish poet and prose writer .
Harold Mattingly ( 1884 - 26 January 1964 ) was a British art historian and numismatist , who specialised in the history of Ancient Rome , especially Etruscan and Roman currency .
Abdolreza Rajabi ( 1962 -- 30 October 2008 ) was a Kurdish Iranian , born in Mahidasht District , west of the Kermanshah Province .
Arthur Dallidet ( 12 October 1906 -- 30 May 1942 ) was a French metal worker , Communist and trade union leader in the Renault factories , who became a leader of the French Resistance during World War II ( 1939 - -45 ) .
Gerry Anderson , MBE ( born Gerald Alexander Abrahams ; 14 April 1929 -- 26 December 2012 ) was an English television and film producer , director , writer and occasional voice artist .
Owen Francis Dudley ( 1882 - 1952 ) was an English Catholic priest who gained fame both as a world lecturer and as a novelist .
Geoffrey Kingscott ( 1936 -- 2 March 2011 ) was a British writer , journalist , editor , translator , and UKIP politician .
Gilly Flower ( 26 August 1908 - February 2001 ) was an English actress , best remembered as the elderly Miss Abitha Tibbs in the cult BBC sitcom Fawlty Towers .
Vice - Admiral The Honourable Edmund Rupert Drummond CB MVO DL ( 8 May 1884 -- 9 September 1965 ) was a Royal Navy officer who became Commander - in - Chief of the New Zealand Division .
Antoine d'Estrées ( 1529 -- 11 May 1609 ) was Marquis of Coeuvres , vicomte of Soissons and of Bercy , Knight of the Order of Saint - Esprit ( 1578 ) and Knight of the Order of Saint - Michel ( 1578 ) .
Bhabani Bhattacharya ( 10 November 1906 - -10 October 1988 ) was an Indian writer , of Bengali origin , who wrote social - realist fiction .
Izidor Papo ( 31 December 1913 -- 14 October 1996 ) was a surgeon , general , military medical chief and academician .
Henry Medley ( 1687 -- 5 August 1747 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy , rising to the rank of vice - admiral .
Alberto Pigaiani ( 15 July 1928 -- 15 June 2003 ) was an Italian heavyweight weightlifter .
Ascanio Vitozzi ( also spelled Ascanio Baschi di Vitozzo or Vittozzi ) ( 1539 - -1615 ) was an Italian soldier , architect and military engineer .
Wilhelm Jürgensen ( 1762 in Schleswick -- 1842 ) was a Norwegian military officer .
Sarah Grand ( 10 June 1854 -- 12 May 1943 ) was an Irish feminist writer active from 1873 to 1922 .
Ognjeslav Kostović Stepanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Огњеслав Костовић Степановић ) ( 1851 -- 16 December 1916 ) was a Serbian inventor .
Niels Ludvig Westergaard ( 27 October 1815 -- 9 September 1878 ) was a Danish Orientalist born in København .
Carl Plötz ( 1814 - 12 August 1886 , Greifswald ) was a German entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera and in particular Hesperiidae .
Rev. Sir James Stronge , 1st Baronet ( 1750 -- 1 December 1804 ) was born in Tynan Abbey , County Armagh , Ireland .
Billie Fleming , known at the time as Billie Dovey ( 13 April 1914 -- 12 May 2014 ) , was a long distance cyclist who set the woman 's record for greatest distance cycled in a year in 1938 at 29,603.7 miles ( 47,642.5 km ) .
Bernard Flexner ( 1882 - -1946 ) , a New York lawyer , was a prominent member of the Zionist Organization of America .
Adolph Verschueren ( also Adolf ; 10 June 1922 -- 30 April 2004 ) was a Belgian cyclist .
Lin Zexu ( 30 August 1785 -- 22 November 1850 ) , courtesy name Yuanfu , was a Chinese scholar and official of the Qing dynasty , hailing from Fuzhou , Fujian province .
Constantin J. David ( 18 February 1886 - 19 February 1964 ) was a German journalist , film director , film producer , and actor .
Elisabeth Olin née Lillström ( December 1740 -- 26 March 1828 ) , was a Swedish opera singer and a music composer .
William Wolryche - Whitmore ( 16 September 1787 -- 11 August 1858 ) was a Shropshire landowner and British Whig politician .
Marco Bucci ( 29 November 1960 -- 6 August 2013 ) was an Italian discus thrower .
Indra Pala ( 960 - 990 ) was ruler of Pala Dynasty ( 900 - -1100 ) of Kamarupa Kingdom .
María Luisa Martínez de García Rojas ( 1780 -- 1817 ) was an insurgent and heroine of the Mexican War of Independence .
Angiolo Torchi ( Massa Lombarda , Lombardy , November , 1856 - 1915 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of landscapes .
William Ayling ( born 1766 and christened 30 September 1766 at Cocking , Sussex ; died October 1826 at Bromley , Kent ) was an English professional cricketer who made 22 known appearances in major cricket matches from 1800 to 1810 ; followed by a further 3 in 1825 and 1826 .
Major General Christopher Vokes CB , CBE , DSO , CD ( 13 April 1904 - -27 March 1985 ) was a senior Canadian Army officer who fought in World War II .
Luis González Velázquez ( August 25 , 1715 -- May 24 , 1763 ) , was a Spanish late - Baroque painter .
Maria Eleonore of Liechtenstein ( Oettingen , 7 July 1745 - Vienna , 26 November 1812 ) was a princess of Liechtenstein and a politically influential Austrian salonist .
Davitt Coghlan ( 28 December 1907 -- 10 October 1964 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
George Musgrove ( 21 January 1854 -- 21 January 1916 ) was an English - born Australian theatre producer .
John Somerville , 3rd Lord Somerville ( died 1491 ) was the son of William Somerville , 2nd Lord Somerville and Janet Mowat .
Ermenegildo Agazzi ( 24 July 1866 -- 25 October 1945 ) was an Italian painter , active in painting genre , portraits , and landscapes .
Francis Jourdain ( 2 November 1876 -- 31 December 1958 ) was a painter , furniture maker , interior designer , maker of ceramics , and other decorative arts , and a left - wing political activist .
Clarissa Dickson Wright ( 24 June 1947 -- 15 March 2014 ) was an English celebrity chef , television personality , writer , businesswoman , and former barrister ( the youngest person to be called to the Bar at the time ) .
Griffiths Mxenge , ( 27 February 1935 -- 19 November 1981 ) was a South African anti - apartheid activist .
The Right Reverend Ludlow Tonson , 3rd Baron Riversdale DD ( 6 March 1784 -- 13 December 1861 ) , was a Church of Ireland bishop .
Comentiolus ( Greek : Κομεντίολος , Komentiolos ; died 602 ) was a prominent Eastern Roman ( Byzantine ) general at the close of the 6th century during the reign of Emperor Maurice ( r. 582 - -602 ) .
Eregzengiin Choidog ( Mongolian : Эрэгзэнгийн Чойдог ; October 10 . 1926 - 1988 ) is one of Mongolia 's best known composers .
Eula Pearl Carter Scott ( 1915 - -2005 ) became the youngest pilot in the United States on September 12 , 1929 , when she took her first solo flight .
Dr David Stark Murray ( 14 July 1900 -- 16 September 1977 ) , son of Robert Murray MP was a consultant pathologist , author , and President of the Socialist Medical Association 1951 - -70 .
John Buxton Hilton was a British crime writer ( 1921 - -1986 ) .
Joseph Mason Cox ( 1763 - -1818 ) was an early nineteenth century English physician whose entire professional career was devoted to care and treatment of mentally ill people .
Eloy Tarazona ( 1880 - -1953 ) was a Venezuelan military figure known by his nickname `` The Indian Tarazona '' .
Ari Ankorion ( Hebrew : ארי אנקוריון‎ , born Ari Wolowitzky , 2 October 1908 -- 11 March 1986 ) was an Israeli politician and lawyer .
Leonard Burt , CVO , CBE ( 1892 - 1983 ) was a British police officer , involved in several high - profile cases and investigations .
Auguste - Savinien Leblond d'Olblen ( 19 October 1760 -- 22 February 1811 ) was a French mathematician and the inventor of the unit of measurement , the metre .
Gar Tsenye Dompu ( Tibetan : མགར་བརྩན་སྙ་ལྡོམ་པུ , Wylie : mgar brtsan snya ldom pu ; ? -- 685 ) was a general of the Tibetan Empire .
Thomas Stanley Westoll , FRS FRSE , FGS ( 3 Jul 1912 -- 19 Sep 1995 ) was the long - time head of the Department of Geology at Newcastle University .
Richard Oakeley ( died 1653 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1624 .
Edward Charles Richard Taaffe ( 1898 - -1967 ) , known as Richard , was an Austrian gemmologist who found the first cut and polished taaffeite in November 1945 .
Thomas Glaholm ( 1834 - 1888 ) was the son of a Newcastle steam flour miller .
Arnold Ludwig Gotthilf Heller ( May 1 , 1840 - 1913 ) was a German anatomist and pathologist who was a native of Kleinheubach am Main , Bavaria .
Harry Brereton ( 13 June 1887 -- 31 December 1950 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Benjamin Garlike ( c. 1766 -- 14 May 1815 , Albany , London ) was a British diplomat , ambassador to Denmark and Prussia .
José Rafael Revenga y Hernández ( 24 November 1786 -- 9 March 1852 ) was a minister of foreign affairs of Gran Colombia ( 1819 - -1821 ) .
Harry Källström ( 30 June 1939 - 13 July 2009 ) , nicknamed `` Sputnik '' , was a Swedish professional rally driver who debuted in 1957 and competed in the World Rally Championship in the 1970s .
False Margaret ( or Margareth or Margareta ) ( c. 1260 -- 1301 ) was a Norwegian woman who impersonated Margaret , Maid of Norway .
Madame Céleste or Madame Céline Céleste ( 16 August 1815 , Paris -- 12 February 1882 , Paris ) was a French dancer and actress .
Mary Chilton ( 1607 -- c . April 1679 ) was a Pilgrim and purportedly the first European woman to step ashore at Plymouth , Massachusetts .
Armagil Waad ( or Armigill Wade ) ( ca . 1511 -- 20 June 1568 ) was a chief clerk of the Privy Council , servant of government and an English parliamentarian .
Jwala Prasad Kureel ( 15 July 1915 -- 25 February 1991 ) was MP of the 6th Lok Sabha in 1977 , affiliated to Janata Party .
Charles - Pierre Boullanger ( 1772 - 1813 ) was a French geographer who served on Nicolas Baudin 's scientific expedition to the South Seas from 1800 to 1803 .
Ingjald Nissen ( 2 September 1896 -- 25 February 1977 ) was a Norwegian psychologist and philosopher .
Frank McCabe ( March 10 , 1859 -- 1924 ) was an American jockey and a Hall of Fame trainer of Thoroughbred racehorses .
Lawrence Bede Fanning ISO ( 18 August 1885 -- 14 August 1970 ) was a senior Australian public servant , best known for his time as Director - General of the Postmaster - General 's Department in the 1940s .
Ahmad Nadeem Qasmi ( Urdu : احمد ندیم قاسمی‎ ) born Ahmad Shah Awan(Urdu : احمد شاہ اعوان‎ ) on 20 November 1916 -- died 10 July 2006 , was an Urdu and English language Pakistani poet , journalist , literary critic , dramatist and short story author .
Dorothy Mayhall ( 1925 - -1995 ) was an American museum director and sculptor .
Mitja Brodar ( 1921 -- 16 February 2012 ) was a Slovenian archaeologist .
Caroline Keer , RRC & Bar ( born 1857 -- died 29 December 1928 ) was a British military nurse and nursing administrator , who served in Natal during the Boer War .
The Blessed Bernhard Lichtenberg ( 3 December 1875 -- 5 November 1943 ) was a German Roman Catholic priest and theologian , who died while in the custody of forces of the Third Reich .
Edward Caldwell Moore ( 1857 - -1943 ) was an American theologian , brother of George Foot Moore and Frank Gardner Moore .
Alfonso Patiño Rosselli ( 1923 -- 7 November 1985 ) was a Colombian jurist and diplomat who died in the 1985 Palace of Justice Siege by the M-19 where he was a Magistrate and President of the Constitutional Chamber of the Supreme Court of Colombia .
Johann Karl Thilo ( Langensalza , near Erfurt , 28 November 1794 -- Halle 17 May 1853 ) was a German theologian and biblical scholar .
Charles Caleb Colton ( 1780 - -1832 ) was an English cleric , writer and collector , well known for his eccentricities .
Lorna Arnold OBE ( 7 December 1915 -- 25 March 2014 ) was a British historian who wrote a number of books connected with the British nuclear weapons programmes .
Henry Ercole ( died 1764 ) was a minor Maltese mediaeval philosopher who specialised mainly in ethics and logic .
Seoán Ó Máel Fogmair was Bishop of Killala until 25 October 1280 .
Percy Radcliffe ( 1916 - -1991 ) was a Member of the Legislative Council of the Isle of Man , and Chairman of the Executive Council from 1971 until 1977 , and from 1981 to 1985 .
Sir William Papworth ( c.1331 - 1414 ) , of Grafham , ( then in Huntingdonshire , now Cambridgeshire ) and Papworth St. Agnes , Cambridgeshire , was an English politician .
Pál Várhidi ( born Pál Vinkovics , 6 November 1931 -- 12 November 2015 ) was a Hungarian football player and a manager .
Ashok Kumar Sarkar ( 7 October , 1912 -- 17 February , 1983 ) was the editor - in - chief and owner of Anandabazar Patrika and ABP Group from 1958 to 1983 after death of Prafulla Kumar Sarkar the inaugural editor of Anandabazar Patrika .
Richard St Lawrence , 7th Baron Howth ( c.1510 - 1558 ) was an Anglo - Irish nobleman and military commander .
Michael Špaček ( Montélimar , France 2 March 1991 - Plzeň 12 October 2009 ) was a Czech youth motocross champion .
Robert James McMordie , QC ( 31 January 1849 -- 25 March 1914 ) was an Irish barrister , politician , and Lord Mayor of Belfast .
Edward Tyson ( 20 January 1651 -- 1 August 1708 ) was a British scientist and physician , commonly regarded as the founder of modern comparative anatomy , which compares the anatomy between species .
Adam Forster aka Carl August von Wiarda ( 5 April 1848 Emden , East Frisia - 11 April 1928 Sydney ) , was a botanical illustrator and naturalist , who after a lengthy stay in South Africa , eventually emigrated to Australia .
Demas Dean ( October 6 , 1903 , ( Sag Harbor , New York ) -- 1991 ) was an American jazz trumpeter .
Jack Woolgar ( 15 September 1913 -- 14 July 1978 ) was a British character actor working in television and film in the 1960s and 1970s .
Charles Sackville , 6th Earl of Dorset and 1st Earl of Middlesex , KG ( 24 January 1638 -- 29 January 1706 ) was an English poet and courtier .
Magdalena Roghman ( 1637 -- 1679 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age engraver .
Eliel Soisalon - Soininen ( born Johnsson , risen to the nobility as Soisalon - Soininen ) ( 26 May 1856 -- 6 February 1905 ) , was a Finnish Chancellor of Justice .
Woldemar Hottenroth ( 20 August 1802 , Dresden - 6 September 1894 , Dresden ) was a German portrait , landscape and genre painter in the Late - Romantic style .
Edward Conway , 1st Viscount Conway PC ( 1564 -- 3 January 1631 ) was an English soldier and statesman .
Páidí Ó Sé ( US /ˌpædiː oʊ ˈʃeɪ/ ; Irish : ( ˌpˠaːdʲiː oː ˈʃeː ) ; 16 May 1955 -- 15 December 2012 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer and manager who played as a right half - back for Kerry .
Anastasios Polyzoidis ( Greek : Αναστάσιος Πολυζωίδης , 1802 - -1873 ) was a Greek politician and judicial official .
Marcel Couraud ( born October 20 , 1912 in Limoges , † 14 September 1986 ) was a French conductor .
Felix Dennis ( 27 May 1947 -- 22 June 2014 ) was an English publisher , poet , spoken - word performer and philanthropist .
Johnny Houlston ( 1917 - 1962 ) was a Welsh welterweight and middleweight boxer .
Geunchogo of Baekje ( 324 - 375 , r. 346 - 375 ) was the 13th king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Anders Lindstedt ( 27 June 1854 -- 16 May 1939 ) was a Swedish mathematician , astronomer , and actuarial scientist , known for the Lindstedt - Poincaré method .
Sun Yirang ( Chinese : 孫詒讓 ; pinyin : Sūn Yíràng ) ( 1848 - -1908 ) was a Chinese philologist .
Diana Nasution ( 5 April 1958 -- 4 October 2013 ) , was a very popular Indonesian singer and actress in the 1970s and 1980s .
Paul Borchardt ( 1886 - -1953 ) was a German archaeologist , a pupil of the geographer Siegfried Passarge .
Dr. Wacław Olszak ( 29 May 1868 -- 11 September 1939 ) was a Polish physician , activist and politician from the region of Zaolzie , Czechoslovakia .
Benjamin Woodbridge ( 1622 - -1684 ) was an English clergyman and controversialist , Harvard College 's first - ever graduate , and participant in the Savoy Conference .
Robert Ker ( August 14 , 1824 -- 11 or 12 February 1879 ) was the first Auditor General of the Colony and then the Province of British Columbia .
Willard Fuller ( 1915 - 2009 ) was an American faith healer and proponent of psychic dentistry .
Arthur William à Beckett ( 25 October 1844 -- 14 January 1909 ) was an English journalist and intellectual .
Eric Fitch Daglish ( 1892 - -1966 ) was a British engraver and author .
Duvvuri Venkata Ramana Shastri ( Telugu : దువ్వురి వెంకట రమణ శాస్త్రి ) ( 1897 -- 1972 ) , popularly known as the Kalaprapurna Duvvuri was a Telugu - Sanskrit Scholar of the 20th century .
Ibn Marzuban later died in 1006 at Shustar .
Christian Sparre ( 30 July 1859 -- 4 November 1940 ) was a Norwegian Commanding Admiral and Member of Parliament .
Christopher Caudwell is the pseudonym of Christopher St John Sprigg ( 20 October 1907 -- 12 February 1937 ) , a British Marxist writer , thinker and poet .
Alan Handley ( 11 March 1912 -- 5 January 1990 ) was an American producer and director of television programmes .
Archange de Lyon ( secular name Michael Desgranges ) ( b. at Lyon , 2 March 1736 ; d. there 13 October 1822 ) was a French Capuchin theologian and preacher .
Lucila Gamero de Medina ( 12 June 1873 -- 23 January 1964 ) was a Honduran romantic novelist .
James William Chappell ( 25 March 1915 -- 3 April 1973 ) also known as Jim Chappell and Jimmy Chappell , is a former ice hockey player who mainly played in the English National League ( ENL ) .
Michel Klyne ( 2 July 1781 -- 1868 ) was an employee of the North West Company and later the Hudson 's Bay Company , serving as postmaster at Jasper House in the Rocky Mountains .
James Grenfell Mauldon MC ( known as Jim Mauldon ) ( 1920 -- 21 May 2002 ) was a British mathematician who taught at the University of Oxford and in the United States at Amherst College .
Tommy Blenkinsopp ( born 13 May 1920 ; died 2004 ) was an English footballer , who played for Grimsby Town , Middlesbrough and Barnsley .
Peter Proudfoot ( 25 November 1882 -- 4 March 1941 ) was a Scottish footballer who scored 21 goals in 162 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City , Clapton Orient , Chelsea and Stockport County .
Aubrey Otis Hampton ( 1900 , Copeville , Texas -- 1955 ) was an American radiologist remembered for describing Hampton 's hump and Hampton 's line .
Benny Sims ( 1924 - -1995 ) was a bluegrass and country musician who played with Flatt and Scruggs , Roy Acuff and Bill Monroe .
Manuel Olivares Lapeña ( 2 April 1909 -- 16 February 1976 ) was a Spanish football striker and manager .
Augustine of Alfeld ( 1480 -- c. 1535 ) was a teacher and Minister Provincial of the Franciscan Order in Saxony , who was opposed to Martin Luther on the question of papal authority .
Solomon Schindler ( 1842 - -1915 ) was a rabbi and author .
William J. Butler ( 1860 -- 27 January 1927 ) was an Irish silent film actor .
Guillaume Le Bé ( French pronunciation : ​(ɡijom lə be ) ; 1525 -- 1598 ) was a French punch cutter and engraver who specialised in Hebrew typefaces .
Frank Pearce Sturm ( 1879 - -1942 ) was an English poet and translator , known for his 1906 translations of Baudelaire ; his short poem Still - heart is a popular favourite .
Henry Fleetwood Sheppard ( London , February 5 , 1824 -- November 1901 ) was an English clergyman .
Walter Stuart Diehl ( 3 December 1893 -- 21 November 1976 ) was an American naval officer and pioneering aeronautical engineer .
John Inett ( 1647 - -1717 ) was an English cleric and church historian .
Ted Besford ( 28 June 1915 -- 12 July 1978 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ernest Lindgren ( 3 October 1910 -- 22 July 1973 ) was a British film archivist and writer .
Clair Alan Brown ( born August 16 , 1903 ; died 1982 ) was an American botanist .
John Atkinson Pendlington ( September 1861 - 15 January 1914 ) was the inventor of a linear scoring system for cricket before 1893 .
Sir Edward Blackett , 2nd Baronet ( 25 October 1649 -- 23 April 1718 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1689 and 1701 .
Lord Robert Montagu PC ( 24 January 1825 -- 6 May 1902 ) , was a British Conservative politician .
Protiva Bose ( also spelled Pratibha Basu ; Bengali : প্রতিভা বসু ) ( March 13 , 1915 -- 13 October 2006 ) was one of the most prolific and widely read Bengali writers of novels , short stories , and essays .
Francisco de Caro ( Spanish pronunciation : ( fɾanˈsisko ðe ˈkaɾo ) , 23 March 1898 -- 31 July 1976 ) , was an Argentinian pianist and composer .
Lothoo Nitharwal ( Hindi : लोठू निठारवाल ) ( 1804 - -1855 ) was a revolutionary freedom fighter of Rajasthan , India .
Rabbi Shmuel Rozovsky ( 1913 - -1979 ) was known as a Talmudic lecturer at the Ponevezh Yeshiva located in Bnei Brak , Israel , and was counted amongst the great rabbis of his generation .
Guido Notari ( 10 May 1893 - 21 January 1957 ) was an Italian actor and radio presenter .
Thomas W. Riley ( 1804 ? -- December 27 , 1872 ) was the twelfth Mayor of Louisville , Kentucky from 1858 to 1859 .
Hans Walter Imhoff ( 25 February 1886 -- 19 March 1971 ) was a Swiss professional footballer , who played as a striker .
Viggo Johansen ( 3 January 1851 -- 18 December 1935 ) was a Danish painter and active member of the group of Skagen Painters who met every summer in the north of Jutland .
Alan Peters OBE ( 17 January 1933 - 11 October 2009 ) was a British furniture designer maker and one of the very few direct links with the Arts and Crafts Movement , having apprenticed to Edward Barnsley .
Jean - Marie Beaudet ( 20 February 1908 -- 19 March 1971 ) was a Canadian conductor , organist , pianist , radio producer , and music educator .
Sir Thomas Marchant Williams , writing name T. Marchant Williams , ( 1845 -- 27 October 1914 ) was a Welsh nationalist , lawyer , and author .
Safiye Ayla Targan , née Safiye Ayla , ( 14 July 1907 -- 14 January 1998 ) was one of the most famous singers of Turkish classical music .
Dag Berggrav ( 17 May 1925 -- 3 May 2003 ) was a Norwegian jurist , civil servant and sports administrator .
Johann Andreas Klindworth ( 11 November 1742 in Göttingen -- 1813 ) was an eighteenth - century mechanic and maker of astronomical instruments .
Hans Bague Jassin ( 31 July 1917 -- 11 March 2000 ) , better known as HB Jassin , was an Indonesian literary critic , documentarian , and professor .
Deng Yang ( 鄧颺 : ? -- 249 ) is an official of the Cao Wei .
Jacobus Trigland ( Triglandius ) ( 22 July 1583 -- 5 April 1654 ) was a Dutch Reformed theologian .
Antoine Dupré ( 1782 - -1816 ) was an early Haitian poet and playwright .
Caius Brediceanu ( born April 25 , 1879 , Lugoj - d. 1953 ) was a Romanian politician and diplomat .
Edwin Warren Moïse ( 1810 - 1868 ) was an American physician and Judge in the Confederate States of America .
Francis Bulkeley Johnson ( 1828 - -1887 ) was member of the Jardine , Matheson & Co. and member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Archpriest Isidor Barndt ( 1816 - 1891 ) , a poet and world traveler from Neisse , Germany , a town in the former state of Silesia , now Nysa , Poland , promoted reunionism and wrote about similarities in faiths in order to overcome splits between Protestants and Catholics in late 19th century Germany .
