Minipenetretus quadraticollis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Minipenetretus .
Van Gelder 's bat ( Bauerus dubiaquercus ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Choco tyrannulet ( Zimmerius albigularis ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family , the tyrant flycatchers .
The Mentawi flying squirrel ( Iomys sipora ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Pycnocoma is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1849 .
The Lobatse hinge - back tortoise ( Kinixys lobatsiana ) is a species of turtle in the Testudinidae family .
Alniphyllum is a genus of three species of flowering plants in the family Styracaceae , native to eastern Asia , from central China south to India and Vietnam .
The African reed warbler or African marsh warbler ( Acrocephalus baeticatus ) is an Old World warbler in the genus Acrocephalus .
Mirza 's eastern moss rat ( Mirzamys norahae ) is a species of rodent endemic to New Guinea .
Macleaniella is a genus of deep - sea limpets in the family Cocculinidae .
The Nacophorini are one of the smaller tribes of geometer moths in the subfamily Ennominae .
The Anisophylleaceae are a small family with four genera , in the order Cucurbitales , according to the APG II . However , it is more isolated from the other suprafamilal clades in this order , while it shows some similarities in flower morphology with the genus Ceratopetalum ( family Cunoniaceae , order Oxalidales ) .
The Mishana tyrannulet ( Zimmerius villarejoi ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Golan Heights blind mole - rat ( Spalax golani ) is a rodent species in the family Spalacidae .
Desmanthus is a genus of flowering plants in the subfamily Mimosoideae of the pea family , Fabaceae .
The Kızılırmak toothcarp or Sultan Sazlığı toothcarp ( Aphanius danfordii ) is a species of killifish belonging to the family Cyprinodontidae .
Trioceros melleri , with the common names Meller 's chameleon and giant one - horned chameleon , is the largest species of chameleon from the African mainland ( i.e. the largest of the chameleons not native to Madagascar ) .
The Australian anchovy , Engraulis australis , is an anchovy of the family Engraulidae , found off south - east Australia , and around New Zealand .
Unknown to her at the time , Carpenter ( 1996 ) had revised the Polycotylidae and separated Dolichorhynchops from Trinacromerum , raising the question as to whether or not the specimens represented a separate species or just larger individuals of D. osborni .
Wielandieae is a tribe of the family Phyllanthaceae .
Aristea is a genus of evergreen , perennial and rhizomatous species of flowering plants in the iris family ( Iridaceae ) , first described in 1789 .
Caecilia is a genus of amphibians in the family Caeciliidae .
The Bourke 's parrot ( Neopsephotus bourkii , formerly known as Neophema bourkii ) , also known as the Bourke 's parakeet , Bourke or `` Bourkie '' , is a small parrot originating in Australia and the only species in its genus Neopsephotus .
Metaxidius brunnipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Metaxidius .
The Zoroasteridae are one of three families of Asteroidea ( sea stars ) in the order Forcipulatida .
Zeugophorinae is a subfamily of beetles within the family Megalopodidae .
Anthocarapa is a monotypic genus of tree in the mahogany family Meliaceae .
Zoianillus acutipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Zoianillus .
Barbarea ( winter cress or yellow rocket ) is a genus of about 22 species of flowering plants in the family Brassicaceae , native to temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere , with the highest species diversity in southern Europe and southwest Asia .
The Aru tree frog ( Litoria aruensis ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
In taxonomy , the Dendroceratida are an order of sponges of the class Demospongiae .
The Arizona cotton rat or Colorado River cotton rat ( Sigmodon arizonae ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Chytridiomycetes is the major class of the phylum Chytridiomycota , which contains a number of parasitic species .
The Rüppell 's weaver ( Ploceus galbula ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Duvalioblemus sichuanicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Duvalioblemus .
Ischnoderma is a genus of polypore fungi in the family Fomitopsidaceae .
Cephise is a Neotropical genus in the family Hesperiidae ( Eudaminae ) .
The Malagasy brush warbler ( Nesillas typica ) , also known as the Madagascar brush - warbler , is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
Patanitretus pakistanensis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Patanitretus .
The Cocos flycatcher ( Nesotriccus ridgwayi ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family , and the only species in the genus Nesotriccus .
Nairovirus is a genus in the family Bunyaviridae that include viruses with circular , negative - sense single stranded RNA .
Dynomenidae is a family of crabs in the superfamily Dromioidea mostly found in Madagascar .
Tsaagan was assigned to the Dromaeosauridae .
Zinken 's tiger ( Parantica albata ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly , endemic to Indonesia .
The Guatemalan helmeted basilisk ( Corytophanes percarinatus ) is a species of lizard in the family Corytophanidae found in Guatemala and southern Mexico .
Goldman 's diminutive woodrat ( Nelsonia goldmani ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Ostracion nasus also known as the Shortnose boxfish is a species of boxfish found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Graham 's gudgeon , Grahamichthys radiata , is a New Zealand sleeper of the family Thalasseleotrididae , the only member of the genus Grahamichthys .
The Rio Grande cooter ( Pseudemys gorzugi ) is a species of turtle in the family Emydidae .
Scopulini as a family name is an old synonym of the subfamily Sterrhinae ( Meyrick , 1892 ) .
The Euparagiinae are a small subfamily of rare wasps in the family Vespidae containing the single genus Euparagia .
Keraea is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrialpulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Discidae , the disc snails .
Bafodeya is a genus of plants in the Chrysobalanaceae family described in 1976 .
Agonoriascus lapidicola is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Agonoriascus .
Paleopsilopterus is an extinct genus of giant flightless predatory birds of the subfamily Psilopterinae of the family Phorusrhacidae , or `` terror birds '' .
Periandra is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family Fabaceae , subfamily Faboideae .
`` Candidatus Brocadia anammoxidans '' is a bacterial member of the order Planctomycetes and therefore lacks peptidoglycan in its cell wall , has a compartmentalized cytoplasm .
Gasconsoceras is a genus of nautiloid cephalopod belonging to the tarphyceroid family Barrandeoceratidae , known from the Middle Silurian .
Thresher sharks are large lamniform sharks of the family Alopiidae found in all temperate and tropical oceans of the world ; the family contains four species , all within the genus Alopias .
Phylloscartes is a genus of small birds in the Tyrannidae family .
The Jamaican spindalis ( Spindalis nigricephala ) is a species of bird formerly in the family Thraupidae .
Carpinus caroliniana ( American hornbeam ) is a small hardwood tree in the genus Carpinus .
The Tabor tree frog , Hyloscirtus lascinius , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia and Venezuela .
Tenodera is a genus of mantis in the subfamily Mantinae of the family Mantidae which contains several species of praying mantises .
The Chilean angelshark ( Squatina armata ) is an angel shark of the family Squatinidae found in the subtropical waters of Chile , that grows up to 1.03 metres ( 3 ft 5 in ) in length .
The Striped bystranka , Alburnoides taeniatus , is a fish species of Cyprinidae family .
Callionymus australis , the Australian stinkfish , is a species of dragonet only found in the Indian Ocean off of northwestern Australia .
The Western Atlantic finless eel ( Apterichtus kendalli , also known as the Finless eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Spondyliaspidinae is a bug subfamily in the family Aphalaridae .
The Rachicerinae are a small subfamily of flies belonging to the family Xylophagidae .
Tainoceratidae forms the larger of the two branches of the superfamily Tainocerataceae derived from the earlier family Rutoceratidae around the end of the Devonian or early in the Mississippian ( Lower Carboniferous ) .
Vagrantini is a tribe of butterflies in the subfamily Heliconiinae found from east Africa over the Indian subcontinent to eastern Asia and Australia .
Caledothele is a spider genus in the funnel - web spiders of family Dipluridae found in Australia .
The Pacific sand sole , Psettichthys melanostictus , is the only fish in the genus Psettichthys of the Pleuronectidae family .
Triplarina is a genus of 7 species of shrubs in the family Myrtaceae .
The Príncipe white - eye ( Zosterops ficedulinus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
The Canada goose ( Branta canadensis ) is a large wild goose species with a black head and neck , white patches on the face , and a brown body .
Bridouxia is a genus of small tropical freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Paludomidae .
The Cameroon forest tree frog , Leptopelis brevirostris , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Cameroon , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , and Nigeria , and possibly the Central African Republic , and the Republic of the Congo .
Rhytidochrotinae is a subfamily of grasshoppers from the family Acrididae with 20 genera and 47 species .
The Gulf crayfish snake ( Regina rigida sinicola ) is a subspecies of nonvenomous snake endemic to the southeastern United States .
Omura 's whale or the dwarf fin whale ( Balaenoptera omurai ) is a species of rorqual about which very little is known .
Blackfin barracuda ( Sphyraena genie ) is a species of barracuda found in parts of Indo - Pacific and Western Pacific .
Chapman 's zebra ( Equus quagga chapmani ) is a subspecies of the plains zebra .
The Malabar trogon ( Harpactes fasciatus ) is a species of bird in the trogon family .
Arthropteris is a small genus of ferns in family Tectariaceae , native to Australia , Europe , Asia and Africa , and previously placed in the families Oleandraceae or Davalliaceae .
Camptidius ophthalmicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Camptidius .
Fangalabola ( Deborrea malgassa ) is a species of bagworm native to Madagascar .
Katepensaurus was assigned to Limaysaurinae , a subfamily of rebbachisaurid diplodocoid , based on the presence of traits that were found to diagnose limaysaurines in previous phylogenetic analyses .
Lonchoptera , a genus of spear - winged flies ( Lonchopteridae ) , are tiny to small ( 2 - 5 mm ) , slender , yellow to brownish - black bristly Diptera .
Grammicosum flavofasciatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Grammicosum .
The taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 categorizes Latouchella in the family Coreospiridae in the superfamilia Scenelloidea within the Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain systematic position .
The Torridincolidae are a small family of beetles in the suborder Myxophaga .
Moriodema mcoyei is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Moriodema .
Aterigena is genus of spiders in the family Agelenidae .
Père David 's mole ( Talpa davidiana ) is a mole found only in Kurdistan Province , Iran .
The Apogoninae are the most species - rich and , of its shape , size , color and habitat , most diverse subfamily of cardinal fish ( Apogonidae ) .
The Hesperiini are a tribe in the Hesperiinae subfamily of skipper butterflies .
The Philippine cuckoo - dove ( Macropygia tenuirostris ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
The Eurasian nuthatch or wood nuthatch ( Sitta europaea ) is a small passerine bird found throughout temperate Asia and in Europe , where its name is the nuthatch .
Saicinae is a subfamily of the family Reduviidae , or the assassin bugs .
Antennommata costata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Antennommata .
Palaeontinidae are currently classified under the extinct superfamily Palaeontinoidea along with the families Dunstaniidae and Mesogereonidae .
Styxosaurus is a genus of plesiosaur of the family Elasmosauridae .
The order Pinales in the division Pinophyta , class Pinopsida , comprises all the extant conifers .
Alexandromys is a subgenus of voles in the genus Microtus .
The Asian golden cat ( Catopuma temminckii , syn . Pardofelis temminckii ) , also called the Asiatic golden cat and Temminck 's cat , is a medium - sized wild cat of Southeastern Asia .
Nectandra is a genus of plant in the family Lauraceae found in South America , and having fruit with various medical effects .
The Sunda cuckoo or Sunda lesser cuckoo ( Cuculus lepidus ) is a South - east Asian bird belonging to the genus Cuculus in the cuckoo family , Cuculidae .
Pseudorbilia is a genus of fungi in the family Orbiliaceae consisting only of the species Pseudorbilia bipolaris .
The Andean gull ( Chroicocephalus serranus ) is a species of gull in the Laridae family .
Propionivibrio is a genus of gram - negative , chemo - organo - trophic , non - spore - forming bacteria from the family of Rhodocyclaceae which belongs to the class of Betaproteobacteria .
Thinocorus is a genus of seedsnipe , a South American family of small gregarious waders which have adapted to a vegetarian diet .
The Gambel 's quail ( Callipepla gambelii ) is a small ground - dwelling bird in the New World quail family .
The Sanje mangabey ( Cercocebus sanjei ) is a highly endangered Old World monkey of the white - eyelid mangabey group from Tanzania .
Khunnuchelys is a turtle that is grouped within Trionychinae , a subfamily of Trionychidae .
Pselaphinae are a subfamily of beetles in the family Staphylinidae , the rove beetles .
The Caucasian pygmy shrew or Ukrainian shrew ( Sorex volnuchini ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Nelson 's pocket mouse ( Chaetodipus nelsoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
The European pond turtle ( Emys orbicularis ) , also called the European pond terrapin , is a long - living freshwater species of turtle .
Tenebrioninae are a large subfamily of the darkling beetles ( Tenebrionidae ) , containing , among others , the flour beetles .
Rhabdoherpia is a genus of solenogaster of uncertain relationship within the order Sterrofustia .
Stirton 's deer mouse ( Peromyscus stirtoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Supachai 's caecilian , Ichthyophis supachaii , is a species of caecilian in the family Ichthyophiidae found in Thailand 's provinces of Nakhon Si Thammarat and Trang , and possibly Malaysia .
Chalcolestes is a small genus of damselfly in the family Lestidae .
The Mauritian turtle dove ( Nesoenas cicur ) is an extinct species of the pigeon genus Nesoenas which was endemic to Mauritius .
Parapantonyssus ipiri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parapantonyssus .
Hotea is a genus of shield - backed bugs belonging to the family Scutelleridae .
Pterocarya , often called wingnuts in English , are trees in the walnut family Juglandaceae .
Calocedrus ( common name incense cedar , alternatively spelled incense - cedar ) is a genus of coniferous trees in the cypress family Cupressaceae first described as a genus in 1873 .
The Rondônia bushbird ( Clytoctantes atrogularis ) is a bird species in the family Thamnophilidae .
Edwards 's pheasant ( Lophura edwardsi ) is a bird of the pheasant family Phasianidae and is endemic to the rainforests of Vietnam .
Acochlidiidae was classified as the only family within the superfamily Acochlidioidea Küthe , 1935 in the taxonomy of Bouchet & Rocroi ( 2005 ) .
The New Zealand lanternshark , Etmopterus baxteri , is a shark of the family Etmopteridae in the order Squaliformes .
Bullata is a genus of small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
The Cuatro Cienegas shiner ( Cyprinella xanthicara ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Madrean alligator lizard ( Elgaria kingii ) is a species of anguid lizard endemic to the southwestern United States and adjacent northwestern Mexico .
The American black swift or more simply black swift ( Cypseloides niger ) is a name given to birds that are found from northern British Columbia in Canada through the United States and Mexico to Costa Rica and Brazil .
The Ocellated turbot , Pleuronichthys ocellatus , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Osteophorus is an extinct genus of eryopoidean euskelian temnospondyl within the family Eryopidae .
The Haloritidae is a family of subglobular , involute , Triassic ammonoids belonging to the ceratitid superfamily Tropitaceae .
The Catabena Moth ( Neogalea sunia ) is a moth of the family Noctuidae , and the only species in the Neogalea genus .
Opeas is a genus of small , tropical , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Subulinidae .
The Turkestanian salamander ( Hynobius turkestanicus ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family once found in Kyrgyzstan , Tajikistan , and Uzbekistan .
The tribe Euglossini , in the subfamily Apinae , commonly known as orchid bees or Euglossine bees , are the only group of corbiculate bees whose non - parasitic members do not all possess eusocial behavior .
Assiminea is a genus of minute , salt - tolerant snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks , or micromollusks , in the family Assimineidae .
Fraxinus cuspidata ( fragrant ash ) is a tree native to northern Mexico and the southwestern United States .
Notochoerus is an extinct genus of very large pig - like animals from the subfamily Tetraconodontinae .
The Mississippi kite ( Ictinia mississippiensis ) is a small bird of prey in the family Accipitridae .
Heteropurpura is an extinct genus of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Adinolepsis is a genus of beetles in the family Cupedidae containing four species , all endemic to Australia .
Nasua is a genus within the family Procyonidae , whose best - known members are raccoons .
Ceropsora is a genus of rust fungus in the family Coleosporiaceae .

The Indochinese hog deer or Thai hog deer ( Hyelaphus annamiticus ) is a species of hog deer native to Cambodia , Laos , People 's Republic of China and Vietnam .
The Réunion seahorse ( Hippocampus borboniensis ) is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family .
Shunosaurus was originally classified as a member of the Cetiosaurinae ; in 1992 Dong assigned it to Shunosaurinae within the Cetiosauridae .
Rhodocharis anacoloides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Rhodocharis .
Cambarellus is a genus of small freshwater crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
The African marsh rat or common dasymys ( Dasymys incomtus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Japanese flying squid , Japanese common squid or Pacific flying squid , scientific name Todarodes pacificus , is a squid of the family Ommastrephidae .
The Tasmanian pademelon ( Thylogale billardierii ) , also known as the rufous - bellied pademelon or red - bellied pademelon , is the sole endemic species of pademelon , marsupials found in Tasmania , and formerly throughout south - eastern Australia .
The New Zealand grayling , Prototroctes oxyrhynchus , is an extinct smelt of the genus Prototroctes , which was found only in lowland rivers and streams of New Zealand .
The genus Mitrephora , of family Annonaceae , comprises around 40 species of small trees and shrubs found in tropical Asia and northern Australasia .
Frommeella ( Frommeëlla ) is a genus of rust fungi in the family Phragmidiaceae .
Dongmolla is a harvestman genus in the family Assamiidae , with only 1 described species - Dongmolla silvestrii .
Certhioidea is a superfamily belonging to the infraorder Passerida containing wrens and their allies .
Nolthenius 's long - tailed climbing mouse ( Vandeleuria nolthenii ) , also known as Sri Lanka highland tree mouse , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Eurasian skylark ( Alauda arvensis ) is a small passerine bird species .
The Raycraft Ranch killifish or Raycraft poolfish , Empetrichthys latos concavus , was first described in 1948 .
The Georgia pigtoe ( Pleurobema hanleyianum ) is a rare species of freshwater mussel in the Unionidae family .
Iridoideae subfamily is one of the two main subfamilies in the popular Iridaceae family .
Although the phylogenetic position of Brasilotitan is difficult to establish , the new species is neither basal nor a derived member of Titanosauria and , based on the lower jaw morphology , appears to be closely related to Antarctosaurus and Bonitasaura .
Arnot 's chat ( Myrmecocichla arnotti ) , also called the white - headed black - chat , is a species of bird in the chat and flycatcher family Muscicapidae .
In the APG III system , adopted here , Hesperocallis is placed in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Agavoideae , since recent molecular systematic studies ( Pires et al . 2004 ) have confirmed a close relationship with Agave .
Phyllocrania is a genus of mantis in the family Hymenopodidae , containing three species , Phyllocrania illudens , Phyllocrania insignis , Phyllocrania paradoxa .
The Warner sucker ( Catostomus warnerensis ) is a rare species of freshwater ray - finned fish in the family Catostomidae .
The Oku mouse shrew ( Myosorex okuensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae endemic to Cameroon .
Mehelya capensis , commonly known as the Cape file snake , is a species of large , non - venomous snake endemic to Africa , belonging to the family Colubridae .
The Sulawesi montane rat ( Taeromys hamatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Ferdinandusa is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rubiaceae , native to the American tropics .
Diapterus is a genus of fish in the family Gerreidae , the mojarras .
Corsyra fusula is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Corsyra .
Psychrobacter is a genus of Gram - negative , osmotolerant , oxidase - positive , psychrophilic or psychrotolerant , aerobic bacteria which belong to the family of Moraxellaceae and the class of Gammaproteobacteria .
In 1951 , Bertelsen moved C. spinulosa into its own family , Centrophrynidae , but retained `` Centrophryne gladisfenae '' in the Oneirodidae under a new genus , Spiniphryne .
Tridenchthoniidae is a family of pseudoscorpions within the superfamily Chthonioidea .
Actinobacteridae is a subclass of bacteria , in the class of Actinobacteria .
Endodontidae is a taxonomic family of very small air - breathing land snails and slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Punctoidea .
Vegrandinia is a genus of medium - sized air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropods in the family Subulinidae .
Band cusk - eel ( Ophidion holbrookii ) is a fish species in the family Ophidiidae .

The Andean white - eared opossum ( Didelphis pernigra ) is an opossum species from South America .
Stylemys ( meaning `` pillar turtle '' ) is the first fossil genus of dry land tortoise belonging to the order Testudines discovered in the United States .
Ceriporia is a widely distributed genus of crust fungi in the family Phanerochaetaceae .
Bustylus is an extinct genus of eutherians in the family Adapisoriculidae .
Victorella is a genus of bryozoans in the family Victorellidae .
The Somali wild ass ( Equus africanus somaliensis ) is a subspecies of the African wild ass .
Mouse - tailed bats are a group of insectivorous bats of the family Rhinopomatidae with only three to six species , all contained in the single genus Rhinopoma .

Clinoceratidae is an extinct family of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod of the order Orthocerida that lived in what would be North America and Europe during the middle Ordovician through early Silurian from 466 - -443.7 mya , existing for approximately 22.3 million years .
Guitonia troglophila is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Guitonia .
The Brazilian gracile opossum ( Gracilinanus microtarsus ) is a species of small opossum from Brazil .
Scopoli 's shearwater ( Calonectris diomedea ) is a bird in the Procellariidae family formerly considered conspecific with Cory 's shearwater ( Calonectris borealis ) .
Mauritius upland forest day gecko ( Phelsuma guimbeaui rosagularis Vinson & Vinson , 1969 ) is a diurnal subspecies of geckos .
The family Physaliidae is monotypic , consisting of only one genus , Physalia .
LaVal 's disk - winged bat ( Thyroptera lavali ) is a species of bat in the family Thyropteridae .
Incilius marmoreus ( formerly Bufo marmoreus , common name Wiegmann 's toad or marbled toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .

Gardiner 's burrowing skink ( Pamelaescincus gardineri ) is the only species ( monotypic ) of the skink genus Pamelaescincus .

Psychopsidae is a family of winged insects of the order Neuroptera .

Stefano Donagrandi ( born September 1 , 1976 in Bormio ) is an ice speed skater from Italy , who won the gold medal in the Team Pursuit at the 2006 Winter Olympics .
Otto Cimrman ( born 1 May 1925 ) is a Czech former ice hockey player who competed in the 1956 Winter Olympics .
Travis Nederpelt ( born 10 June 1985 ) is an Australian competition swimmer from Western Australia and butterfly specialist who represented his country at the 2004 Summer Olympics at Athens and in 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .

Gérard Gropaiz ( 1 August 1943 -- 6 October 2012 ) was a French swimmer who competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .

Paulus af Uhr ( January 25 , 1892 -- April 28 , 1972 ) was a Swedish officer and athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Svetlana Saenko is a Ukrainian born wrestler who represented Moldova at the 2012 Summer Olympics .

Shi Feng ( born 1988 - 11 - 06 in Liaoyang , Liaoning ) is a Chinese swimmer , who competed for China at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .

Jimmy Tremeer ( Leonard Francis Tremeer ; August 1 , 1874 -- October 21 , 1951 ) was an Olympic bronze medallist in the men 's 400 metres hurdles at the 1908 Summer Olympics .
Robert Schurrer ( 24 March 1890 -- 27 November 1972 ) was a French sprinter , who competed at the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Magali Rathier ( born 2 December 1974 in Firminy ) is a French former synchronized swimmer who competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Jaqueline Ferreira was 8th at the -75 kg event in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Mário Xandó de Oliveira Neto known as Xandó ( born July 31 , 1961 ) is a Brazilian former volleyball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics and in the 1984 Summer Olympics .

Roland Wille ( born 1 August 1961 ) is a Liechtenstein athlete who competed for his country at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .
Amir Kumar ( August 10 , 1923 -- January 25 , 1980 ) was an Indian field hockey player who won a gold medal at the 1948 Summer Olympics and the 1956 Summer Olympics .

Paula Mollenhauer ( December 22 , 1908 -- July 7 , 1988 ) was a German athlete who won the bronze medal in the discus throw event at the 1936 Summer Olympics held in Berlin , Germany .
Kitty Chiller ( born 2 October 1964 ) is a former modern pentathlete who represented Australia at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney .
Marie Dorin Habert ( born 19 June 1986 ) is a French biathlete who represented France at the 2010 Winter Olympics .
Lucía Pérez Vizcaíno ( Spanish pronunciation : ( luθi.a peɾeθ ) ; born 5 July 1985 in O Incio , Lugo , Galicia ) is a Spanish singer who represented her country in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011 in Germany with the song `` Que me quiten lo bailao '' .
Jay Rand ( born March 4 , 1950 ) is an American former ski jumper who competed at the 1968 Winter Olympics .
Serhiy Timokhov ( Ukrainian : Сергій Тімохов ; born 9 May 1972 ) is a Ukrainian Olympics sailor that participated in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Martina Grunert ( born 17 May 1949 in Leipzig ) is a retired German swimmer who participated in the 1964 and 1968 Summer Olympics .
Gaby Appel ( born 17 January 1958 in Viersen ) is a German former field hockey player who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
William Lofgren ( February 14 , 1913 -- June 11 , 2004 ) was an American canoer who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Jindřich Krepindl ( born July 6 , 1948 ) is a Czechoslovak handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Juan Fabila Mendoza ( born June 5 , 1944 ) is a former Mexican boxer , who a bronze medal in the bantamweight category ( -- 54 kg ) at the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Charles Gniette was a Belgian field hockey player who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Igor Runov ( Russian : Игорь Рунов , 8 February 1963 -- 11 April 2011 ) was a Russian former volleyball player who competed for the Soviet Union in the 1988 Summer Olympics and for the Unified Team in the 1992 Summer Olympics .
Narcyz Maciaszczyk ( born July 19 , 1929 in Gniezno - December 22 , 1985 in Poznań ) was a Polish field hockey player who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics and in the 1960 Summer Olympics .
Albert P. Andersson ( April 25 , 1902 , Tryde , Scania -- March 5 , 1977 ) was a Swedish gymnastics who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Armand Marcelle ( 10 October 1905 -- 26 December 1974 ) was a French rower who won a silver medal in the coxed pairs at the 1928 Summer Olympics , together with his younger brother Édouard .
Georgina Geikie ( born 6 December 1984 ) is a British sport shooter who competed for Great Britain in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Marvin Dixon ( born on September 9 , 1983 ) is a member of the Jamaica national bobsleigh team and competed in the 2014 Winter Olympics in the two - man bobsled .

Giuseppe Valeriano ( L'Aquila , August , 1542 - Naples , July 15 , 1596 ) was an Italian painter and architect , priest of the Jesuit order , and active in Rome , Spain , and Naples .
Vlaho Getaldić ( also Biagio Ghetaldi ; 22 December 1788 - 27 October 1872 ) was a Dalmatian writer , translator and politician from Dubrovnik .

Born in Paris , Bernard Seurre was a student of the sculptor Pierre Cartellier .
Sir Felix Booth , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 1775 Roydon , Essex -- 24 January 1850 Brighton , Sussex ) was a wealthy UK gin distiller , and promoter of Arctic exploration , with various places in Nunavut , Canada being named after him .
Vincenzo da Filicaja was born in Florence to an ancient and noble family .
Marzio Ginetti ( 6 April 1585 -- 1 March 1671 ) was an Italian Catholic Cardinal and Cardinal Vicar of Rome .
Friedrich von Wieser died on July 22 , 1926 in Salzburg , where he is buried .
Li Tchoan King ( born in China on 6 May 1904 ; died in Toulon on 19 August 1971 ) was a Chinese - born draughts player and former French national champion .
In 1981 , Allyn Joslyn died of heart failure in Woodland Hills in Los Angeles , California , at the age of seventy - nine .
Gustav Schröder ( Hadersleben , September 27 , 1885 -- Hamburg , January 10 , 1959 ) was a sea captain , who is best known for attempting to save 937 German Jews , who were passengers on his ship , the MS St. Louis , from the Nazis in 1939 .
Tadeusz Peiper ( Kraków , May 3 , 1891 -- November 10 , 1969 , Warsaw ) was a Polish poet , art critic , theoretician of literature and one of the precursors of the avant - garde movement in Polish poetry .
Antoine - Charles Vauthier ( 1790 Paris - 1879 Paris ) was a French entomologist , botanist , author and natural history illustrator .
Ernst Heinrich Kneschke ( * 27 August 1798 in Zittau ; † 2 December 1869 in Leipzig ) was a German heraldist , ophthalmologist and writer .
Levin Goldschmidt ( 17 May 1828 , Danzig -- 16 July 1897 , Bad Wilhelmshöhe , today Kassel ) was a German jurist .
Massimo Troiano ( died after April 1570 ) was an Italian Renaissance composer , poet , and a brief , but vivid chronicler of life at the court of Bavaria 's ruler , Duke Albrecht V in the late 1560s , the only period in which Troiano is known to history .
Galvano Fiamma ( 1283 - - Milan 1344 ) was an Italian Dominican and chronicler of Milan .
Lorenzo Nottolini ( May 6 1787 -- September 12 1851 ) was an architect and engineer of the Neoclassic style in Lucca .
Philippe de Broca ( 15 March 1933 , Paris -- 26 November 2004 , Neuilly - sur - Seine ) was a French movie director .
Petros Petrosyan was born on December 24 , 1968 in Yerevan in the family of artists Hakob and Vera Petrosyan .
Tom Campbell Black ( December 1899 , Brighton , England -- 19 September 1936 , Liverpool , England ) was a famous English aviator .
Oda Schaefer ( really Oda Lange , born December 21 , 1900 in Berlin - Wilmersdorf as Oda Krus ; died September 4 , 1988 in Munich ) was a German writer and journalist .
Gerhard Fanselau ( 30 April 1904 , Leipzig - 28 April 1982 , Potsdam ) was a German geophysicist .
Elkan Nathan Adler ( 24 July 1861 , St Luke 's , London -- 15 September 1946 , London ) was an English author , lawyer , historian , and collector of Jewish books and manuscripts .
Antonio Téllez Solá ( January 18 , 1921 , Tarragona -- March 27 , 2005 , Perpignan ) was a Spanish anarchist , journalist and historian .
Bernhard Kagan ( 15 August 1866 -- 27 November 1932 , Berlin ) was a German chess player , writer , publisher , editor , and organizer .
Eleonore Wilhelmine of Anhalt - Köthen ( 7 May 1696 in Köthen -- 30 August 1726 in Weimar ) was a princess of Anhalt - Köthen by births and by marriage successively Princess of Saxe - Merseburg and Duchess of Saxe - Weimar .
Howard Smit died at the Providence Tarzana Medical Center on August 1 , 2009 , in Tarzana , California , at the age of 98 .

Nicola Peccheneda ( 1725 , Polla -- 4 November 1804 ) was an Italian painter of Campania and Basilicata in the second half of the 18th century .

Sloane 's viperfish , Chauliodus sloani , is a dragonfish of the genus Chauliodus , found in all tropical and subtropical oceans , at depths down to 2,500 m. Their length is between 20 and 35 cm . As a species , Sloane 's viperfish holds the world record for largest teeth relative to head size in a fish .
Agave attenuata is a species of agave sometimes known as the `` lion 's tail , '' `` swan 's neck , '' or `` foxtail '' for its development of a curved stem , unusual among agaves .

Bletia reflexa is a species of orchid native to Guatemala , Honduras , Chiapas , Oaxaca and Panama .

Crangon allmani , also spelled Crangon allmanni , is a species of shrimp in the genus Crangon .

Clavaria argillacea is a species of mushroom in the Clavariaceae family .
The sole species , Lodoicea maldivica , is endemic to the islands of Praslin and Curieuse in the Seychelles .
Flacourtiaceae is a defunct family of flowering plants whose former members have been scattered to various families , mostly to Achariaceae , Samydaceae , and Salicaceae .
Huoshanornis is a genus of enantiornithine birds which existed in what is now Jiufotang Formation of Western Liaoning Province , China during the early Cretaceous period .
Dinopanorpidae is a small family of extinct insects in the order Mecoptera ( scorpionflies ) that contains two genera and seven species .
Myxodagnus macrognathus is a species of sand stargazer that is known to occur off the Pacific coasts of Mexico and Peru .
Mimoleprodera granulosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimoleprodera .
Mimotroea cacioides is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , and the only species in the genus Mimotroea .
Microbiota is a monotypic genus of evergreen coniferous shrub in the cypress family Cupressaceae , containing only one species , Microbiota decussata ( Siberian carpet cypress , Russian arbor - vitae ) .
Pituophis catenifer affinis , commonly known as the Sonoran gopher snake , is a subspecies of nonvenomous colubrid endemic to the southwestern United States .
Glomeris marginata is a common European species of pill millipede .
Nebria rubicunda is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Algeria , Morocco , Tunisia and in Spain .
Keichousaurus is a genus of marine reptile in the pachypleurosaur family which went extinct at the close of the Triassic in the Triassic - Jurassic extinction event .
Oxypetalum is a genus of flowering plants in the Apocynaceae family , first described with this name in 1810 .
Allium nanodes is a plant species native to the Sichuan and Yunnan regions of southern China .
Diloma arida is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae .
Sesleria is a Eurasian and North African genus of perennial plants in the grass family .
Menegazzia terebrata is a species of lichen found scattered across the Northern Hemisphere .
Acer miaotaiense ( syn . Acer miyabei subsp . miaotaiense ( P.C.Tsoong ) E.Murray ) is a species of maple native to China , in southeastern Gansu , southwestern Henan , northwestern Hubei , southern Shaanxi , and Zhejiang .
Pararcus is an extinct genus of placodont marine reptile from the Middle Triassic of the Netherlands .
Brickellia greenei is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Greene 's brickellbush .
Eranthis hyemalis is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae , native to woodland habitats in Europe .
Otothyris lophophanes is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the coastal streams of Rio de Janeiro State .
Spirillum minus is a species of Spirillum .
Diplomystes camposensis is a species of velvet catfish endemic to Chile where it occurs in the Valdivia region .
Arthrostylidium is a Neotropical genus of climbing bamboo in the grass family .
Gymnitidae is a family of Lower to Middle Triassic ammonite cephalopods with evolute , discoidal shells .
Cantharellus spectaculus is a species of fungus in the genus Cantharellus .
The Cynareae are a tribe of flowering plants in the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
It is monotypic with Nothobachia ablephara as the sole species .
Sorbus aria ( syn . Aria nivea ) , the whitebeam or common whitebeam , is a European and Near - Eastern deciduous tree , the type species of the subgenus of the whitebeams .
Dalbergia funera ( the Ebano or Funera ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Paralaoma servilis is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Punctidae , the dot snails .
Monotomidae is a family of beetles in the suborder Polyphaga , containing the following genera :
Plesiosuchus is an extinct genus of geosaurine metriorhynchid crocodyliform known from the Late Jurassic ( late Kimmeridgian to early Tithonian stage ) of Dorset , England and possibly also Spain .
Platymantis vitiensis ( common names : Fiji tree frog , Levuka wrinkled ground frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Belontia signata , the Ceylonese combtail , is a species of gourami endemic to Sri Lanka .
Blastophaga psenes is a wasp species in the genus Blastophaga .
Tachina barbata is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Tajikistan .
Trifolium montanum , the mountain clover , is a plant species of the genus Trifolium .
Tradescantia crassula , common names succulent spiderwort and white - flowered tradescantia , is a species of plants in the Commelinaceae .
Cyrtopora is an extinct genus from a class of marine Bryozoans , the cyclostomes .
Lochmodocerus antennatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lochmodocerus .
Othnielosaurus is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur that lived about 155 to 148 million years ago , during the Late Jurassic - age Morrison Formation of the western United States .
Cronicombra granulata is a species of sedge moths in the genus Cronicombra .
Tineola is a genus of moths the family Tineidae .
Caridina dennerli is a small species of freshwater shrimp from Sulawesi ( Indonesia ) that grows up to 2.5 centimetres ( 1.0 in ) in length .
Euphorbia cornigera ( horned spurge ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae , native to Bhutan .
The Exoschizonidae are a family in the phylum Apicomplexa .
Verpa is a genus of ascomycete fungi related to the morels .
Solidago auriculata , commonly called clasping goldenrod or eared goldenrod , is a species of flowering plant native to the southeastern and south - central United States from South Carolina west as far as eastern Texas and southeastern Oklahoma .
Paranomus is a genus of 18 species of plants , commonly known as `` sceptres '' , in the protea family .
Berberis argentinensis is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1921 .
Iheringichthys is a small genus of long - whiskered catfish native to South America .
Ophiomorus latastii is a species of skink , a lizard in the family Scincidae .
Tenthredo livida is a sawfly species belonging to the family Tenthredinidae ( common sawflies ) , subfamily Tenthredininae .
Synbranchus marmoratus , the marbled swamp eel , neotropical swamp eel , marmorated swamp eel or mottled swamp eel is a species of swamp eel native to Central and South America .
Picea orientalis , commonly known as the Oriental spruce or Caucasian spruce , is a species of spruce native to the Caucasus and adjacent northeast Turkey .
Paretroplus lamenabe is a species of cichlid from the lower part of the Mahajamba River and Lake Tseny in northwestern Madagascar .
Lycium brevipes is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common name Baja desert - thorn .
Glomerales is an order of symbiotic fungi within the phylum Glomeromycota .
Wrightia antidysenterica is sometimes confused with the species Holarrhena pubescens due to a second , taxonomically invalid publication of the name Holarrhena pubescens .
Ceratopteridaceae is an improper family name for the clade that is now known to include the two genera Ceratopteris and Acrostichum .
Chromodoris strigata , is a species of colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Bagauda zigzag is a species of assassin bug discovered in Taiwan in 2007 in an area of uplifted coral reef forest .
Bayerotrochus boucheti is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Macleaya cordata , the five - seeded plume - poppy , is a species of flowering plant in the poppy family Papaveraceae , which is used ornamentally .
Dubautia kenwoodii ( Kalalau rim dubautia ) is an `` extremely rare '' species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Eucalyptus gomphocephala is a species of tree , also known as Tuart , in the genus Eucalyptus .
Clermontia peleana is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Pele clermontia .
Haplocheirus is a genus of alvarezsauroid theropod dinosaur .
Microlipophrys is a genus of combtooth blennies found in Atlantic ocean and the Mediterranean sea .
Hygroaster is a genus of mushroom - forming fungi in the family Hygrophoraceae .
Disocactus flagelliformis or ( Rattail Cactus ) is a species of Cactaceae and is the most cultivated species in the genus .
Calenduleae is a flowering plant tribe of the family Asteraceae .
Xanthoparmelia lavicola is a species of lichen from Parmeliaceae family that can be found in Arizona , California , and Ecuador .
Cryptogramma cascadensis is a species of fern known by the common names Cascade parsley fern and Cascade rockbrake .
In Linnaean taxonomy , Sauropodomorpha ( which means `` lizard feet forms '' ) is either a suborder or is left unranked .
Aspidistra yingjiangensis is a species of Aspidistra that is found in China .
Brychius pacificus is a species of beetle in the genus Brychius that was discovered in 1928 .
Aleeta is a monotypic genus of Cicada , containing A. curvicosta , found in Australia .
Marasmius midnapurensis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Marasmiaceae that was first described scientifically in 2014 .
Didinium is a genus of unicellular ciliate protists with at least ten accepted species .
Cuscuta salina is a species of dodder known by the common name salt marsh dodder .
Pariproca spinipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pariproca .
Staphylinus is a genus of rove beetles .
Citharus linguatula , the spotted flounder or Atlantic spotted flounder , is a species of fish in the Citharidae , a family of flounders .
Rosa fedtschenkoana is a species in the plant genus Rosa in the family Rosaceae .
Boerhavia intermedia is a species of spiderling plant known by the common name five - wing spiderling .
Lirularia parcipicta , common name the few - spot lirularia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Phacelia vallis - mortae is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common name Death Valley phacelia .
Aenictus ceylonicus is a species of reddish brown army ant found in Southern India , Sri Lanka , Southeast Asia and Australia .
Nassarius kraussianus , common name the tick shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Temnolamia flavosignata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Temnolamia .
Argyrodella is a monotypic genus of tangle - web spider , containing the species Argyrodella pusillus .
Petrochromis macrognathus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers areas with rocky substrates where it can graze on algae .
Philodromus buxi is a spider species found from Europe to Kazakhstan .
Parastathmodera bothai is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parastathmodera .
Phidippus femoratus is a species of spider in the Salticidae family , that can be found in the US states of New Mexico , Arizona and California .
Iris tectorum ( also known as roof iris , Japanese roof iris and wall iris ) is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Limniris .
Conus fumigatus , common name the smoky cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cyathea lepidoclada is a species of tree fern native to central and eastern New Guinea , where it is locally common in rain forest and mossy forest at an altitude of 200 - -1000 m. The trunk of this species is erect and usually 2 - -3 m tall .
Plotosus canius is a species of eeltail catfishes , in the genus Plotosus , native to the Indian Ocean , the western Pacific Ocean and New Guinea .
Lepanthopsis melanantha , common name tiny orchid , is a very small epiphytic species of orchid .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Physalosporopsis rhizophoricola .
Pachyteuthis is a genus of belemnite that lived from the Early Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous , and has been found in Asia and Europe .
Tetracentron is a genus of flowering plant , the sole living species being Tetracentron sinense .
Bitis arietans is a venomous viper species found in savannah and grasslands from Morocco and western Arabia throughout Africa except for the Sahara and rain forest regions .
Haptoclinus dropi , the Four - fin blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny only known to occur off of Curaçao in the Caribbean where it was collected from a deep - sea reef at a depth between 157 and 167 metres ( 515 and 548 ft ) .
Sporobolus contractus is a species of grass known by the common name spike dropseed .
Scrobicaria is a genus of South American plants in the groundsel tribe within the daisy family .
Oreophryne furu is a species of microhylid frog endemic to Western New Guinea , distinguished from other related species by its small size , unique call and egg - guarding behaviour .
Crescentia alata ( variously called Mexican calabash , jícaro , morro , morrito , winged calabash ) is a species in the trumpet - flower family Bignoniaceae and in the calabash trees genus Crescentia , native to southern Mexico and Central America south to Costa Rica .
Benthoclionella jenneri , common name Jenner 's turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Anolis bimaculatus , the panther anole , is a species of anole lizard that is endemic to the Caribbean Lesser Antilles .
Cymbopogon elegans is a grass species in the genus Cymbopogon .
Oncidium geertianum is a species of native to central and southwestern Mexico .
Inanidrilus carterensis is a species of marine Annelid worm .
Angionychus lividus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Angionychus .
Nypa fruticans , commonly known as the nipa palm , is a species of palm native to the coastlines and estuarine habitats of the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Redlichia takooensis is a species of redlichiid trilobite from the lower Cambrian - aged Emu Shale of Kangaroo Island , Australia .
Saharastega is a genus of prehistoric amphibian which lived during the late Permian period , around 251 to 260 million years ago .
Herina scutellaris is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in most of Western Europe .
Meriones tristrami , known as Tristram 's jird , is a species of gerbil that lives in the Middle East .
Cnodalon viride is a species of darkling beetles in the family Tenebrionidae .
Paranaches simplex is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paranaches .
Heterometrus longimanus , the Black Emperor Scorpion or Asian forest scorpion , is a species of scorpions belonging to the family Scorpionidae .
Austrophlebia costalis , the southern giant darner , is a species of dragonfly endemic to Australia .
Gagea kunawurensis is an Asian species of plants in the lily family .
Conta is a small genus of South Asian river catfishes native to India and Bangladesh .
The Cowslip Orchid or Butter Orchid ( Caladenia flava ) is species of orchid found across Southwest Australia .
Sinomeganeura is an extinct genus of griffenfly in the family Meganeuridae and containing a single species Sinomeganeura huangheensis .
Uromycladium tepperianum is a rust fungus that infects over 100 species of Acacia and related genera including Paraserianthes in Australia , south - east Asia , the south Pacific and New Zealand .
Microhyla mantheyi ( common name : Manthey 's narrow - mouthed frog ) is a species of microhylid frog from the Malay Peninsula ( Narathiwat Province in southern Thailand , peninsular Malaysia , and Singapore ) .
Limnodynastes ( commonly known as the Australian swamp frogs ) is a genus of frog native to Australia , southern New Guinea and some Torres Strait Islands .
Charaxes lydiae is the sole member of the Charaxes lydiae species group
Coluber is a genus of thin - bodied , fast - moving , colubrid snakes commonly known as racers .
Arnica cernua is a species of arnica known by the common name serpentine arnica .
Melanobatrachus is a genus of narrow - mouthed frogs ( Microhylidae family ) that contains a single species , Melanobatrachus indicus .
Solidago squarrosa , commonly known as stout goldenrod , is a North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .
The Trinil tiger ( Panthera tigris trinilensis ) is an extinct tiger subspecies dating from about 1.2 million years ago that was found at the locality of Trinil , Java , Indonesia .
Textularia is a genus of textulariid foraminifera .
Spengelomenia is a genus of cavibelonian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like , marine mollusks .
Pipiza festiva is a species of Hoverfly , from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .

Pareiasaurus is an extinct genus of anapsid reptile from the Permian period .
Ctenarchis is a genus of moths of the Carposinidae family , containing only one species , Ctenarchis cramboides .
Clarkia tembloriensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family , known by the common name Temblor Range clarkia .
Volvox carteri F.Stein 1873 is a species of colonial green algae in the order Volvocales .
Tropidophis taczanowskyi , or Taczanowski 's dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family .
The small Lepidopteran family Douglasiidae includes several species of moths whose adults are collectively called Douglas moths and whose larvae are leaf miners .
Allium giganteum , common name Giant Onion , is an Asian species of onion , native to central and southwestern Asia but cultivated in many countries as a flowering garden plant .
Jasminum malabaricum ( malabar jasmine , wild jasmine ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Oleaceae , native to southern parts of India , and Sri Lanka .
Cicurina venii is a rare species of eyeless spider in the family Dictynidae known by the common name Braken Bat Cave meshweaver .
Cyathea doctersii is a species of tree fern endemic to Sumatra , where it grows in forest at an altitude of approximately 150 m. The trunk is erect and 2 - 3 m tall .
Climacoceratidae ( `` ladder horns '' ) is a family of superficially deer - like artiodactyl ungulates restricted to the Miocene of Africa .
Vanda cristata is a species of orchid found from the Himalaya to China ( northwestern Yunnan ) .
Mesoscincus is a genus comprising three species of skink native to Mexico and Central America .
Eptesicus is a genus of bats , commonly called house bats , in the family Vespertilionidae .
Neolitsea parvigemma is a species of small to medium - sized tree in the Lauraceae family .

Acanthaceae is a family ( the acanthus family ) of dicotyledonous flowering plants containing almost 250 genera and about 2500 species .

Pakicetinae is a subfamily of Pakicetidae of the order Archaeoceti .
Micropterix rablensis is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Zeller in 1868 .
Cirsium remotifolium is a species of thistle known by the common name fewleaf thistle .
Praematoliparis anarthractae is a species of snailfish native to the southeastern Pacific Ocean near Chile where it can be found at depths down to 485 metres ( 1,591 ft ) though usually not deeper than 55 metres ( 180 ft ) .
Lithophila is a genus of plant in family Amaranthaceae .
Pittosporum obcordatum , commonly called Heart - leaved Kohuhu , is a species of plant in the Pittosporaceae family .

Halimeda is a genus of green macroalgae .
Erythrotrichia welwitschii is a red algae species in the genus Erythrotrichia found in South Africa from Cape of Good Hope and False Bay extending eastwards at least as far as Port Elizabeth .
Fromia milleporella , common name red starfish or black spotted starfish , is a species of starfish belonging to the family Goniasteridae .
Clivia nobilis ( green - tip forest lily ) , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Clivia , of the family Amaryllidaceae , native to South Africa .

Oncidium citrinum is a species of orchid found from Colombia to Trinidad .
Gardenia brighamii , commonly known as nānū , naʻu , or forest gardenia , is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , Rubiaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Frasera gypsicola is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common names Sunnyside green - gentian , Sunnyside elkweed , and Sunnyside frasera .

Lepechinia calycina is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name pitchersage or woodbalm .
Sisymbrium loeselii is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by several common names , including small tumbleweed mustard , false London - rocket , and tall hedge mustard .

Artoriopsis expolita is a species of wolf spider from southern Australia .

Cladonia ( cup lichen ) is a genus of moss - like lichens in the family Cladoniaceae .

Phalaenopsis mannii is a species of orchid found from eastern Nepal to southern Yunnan .

Allophylus is a genus within the plant family Sapindaceae .
Psiadia is a genus of Asian and African plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Ectodini is a tribe of cichlids that are endemic to Lake Tanganyika in East Africa .
The flower - feeding march fly , Scaptia auriflua , is a species of horse fly that occurs in Australia .
Clavatula quinteni is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae , first described in 2006 .
Mongolicosa glupovi is a species of wolf spider found in the Russian republics of Altai , Khakassia and Tuva .
Sturisomatichthys caquetae is a species of armored catfish of the family Loricariidae endemic to Colombia where it occurs in the Caquetá River basin .
Nagia promota is a species of moth in the Erebidae family , this species occurs in Madagascar .
Githopsis is a small genus of flowering plants in the bellflower family which are known as bluecups .
Bufo silentvalleyensis ( Silent Valley toad or South Indian hill toad ) , now usually placed in genus Duttaphrynus , is a species of toad endemic to Kerala , southern India .
Fossorochromis rostratus species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
Conus generalis , common name the general cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
It contains only one species , Contralissa catagrapta , which is found in South Africa .
Leucothrinax is a monotypic genus -- it includes only one species , L. morrisii .
Pedostibes rugosus is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Pseudochazara mniszechii ( Herrich - Schaffer , ( 1851 ) ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Coluria is a plant genus in the sub family Rosoideae native to Asia , Siberia and Altai .
Leptoglossus phyllopus or Florida leaf - footed bug is a species of leaf - footed bug in the same genus as the western conifer seed bug ( L. occidentalis ) found throughout the southern United States from Florida to California , through Mexico and as far south as Costa Rica .
Helianthella parryi , Parry 's dwarf - sunflower , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Trichophyton is a genus of fungi , which includes the parasitic varieties that cause tinea , including athlete 's foot , ringworm , jock itch , and similar infections of the nail , beard , skin and scalp .
Paracyprichromis is a small genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Tanganyika in east Africa .
Agyrtidae or primitive carrion beetles are a small family of polyphagan beetles They are found in mostly temperate areas of the northern hemisphere and in New Zealand .
Parapercis alboguttata , the bluenose grubfish , known also as the bluenose sandperch and whitespot sandsmelt , is a species of marine bony fish in the family Pinguipedidae , native to the western Indo - Pacific Ocean .
Malus kansuensis is a species in the genus Malus in the family Rosaceae , called with the common name Calva crabapple .
Alcimochthes is a genus of crab spider found in China , Vietnam , Singapore , Taiwan and Japan .
Lasiorhinus is the genus containing the two hairy - nosed wombats , which are found in Australia .
Pelecocera tricincta is a species of Hoverflies , from the family Syrphidae .
Therippia is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Paratherippia Therippia affinis Breuning , 1938 Therippia latefasciata Breuning , 1936 Therippia mediofasciata Breuning , 1935 Therippia triloba ( Pascoe , 1859 ) subgenus Therippia Therippia decorata Pascoe , 1865 Therippia signata ( Gahan , 1890 )
Acacia eriopoda , commonly known as the Broome pindan wattle is a species of wattle in the legume family that is native to northern Western Australia .
Ramaria rielii is a European species of coral fungus in the family Gomphaceae .
Platycheirus scutatus is a very common species of hoverfly .
Thymistadopsis is a genus of moths belonging to the subfamily Drepaninae .
Coilostylis parkinsoniana ( Parkinson 's Coilostylis ) , formerly Epidendrum parkinsonianum , is an epiphytic species of orchid in the genus Coilostylis , occurring in Mexico and Central America .
Sculptaria is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Plectopyloidea .
Gypospirifer condor is an extinct species of articulate brachiopod fossils belonging to the family Trigonotretidae .
Syzygium leucoxylon is a species of plant in the Myrtaceae family , that grows in the tropical peat swamp forest of Sarawak and Kalimantan .
Fundella pellucens , the Caribbean pod borer , is a species of snout moth in the genus Fundella .
Formotosena montivaga is a cicada species from Southeast Asia that was formerly placed in the genus Tosena .
Neoditrema ransonnetii is a species of surfperch native to the Pacific coasts of Korea and Japan .
Heimia is a genus of flowering plants in the loosestrife family , Lythraceae .
Gluconacetobacter johannae is a species of acetic acid bacteria first isolated from rhizospheres and rhizoplanes of coffee plants .
Zinnia angustifolia , the narrowleaf zinnia , is a herbaceous flowering plant species of zinnia native to northern and western Mexico and naturalized in parts of the Southwestern United States .
Lasmigona costata , common name Flutedshell , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
Rhacophorus robinsonii is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in Malaysia and Thailand .
Crematogaster atitlanica is a species of ant endemic to Guatemala .
It contains the single species Caprimimodes mimetica , which is found in Papua New Guinea .
Provanna abyssalis is a species of abyssal sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Provannidae .
Malosma is a plant genus which contains only a single species , Malosma laurina , with the common names laurel sumac and lentisco ( Spanish ) .
Rhaphithamnus venustus , known locally as Juan Bueno , is a species of plant in the Verbenaceae family .
Treponema carateum is a species of spirochete bacteria in the genus Treponema .
Williams ' jerboa ( Allactaga williamsi ) is a species of jerboas native to Afghanistan , Armenia , Azerbaijan , Iran and Turkey .
Cyathea squamulata is a species of tree fern native to the Malay Peninsula , Sumatra , Java , Borneo and the southern Philippines , including the Sulu Archipelago , where it grows in forest from the lowlands to an altitude of about 1500 m. The trunk is erect and up to 2 m tall .
Pyracantha crenatoserrata is a species of Firethorn .
Sphodromantis rudolfae is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia , Kenya , Somalia , and Zanzibar .
It contains the single species Pachydyptes ponderosus , the New Zealand giant penguin .
Euristhmus is a genus of eeltail catfishes native to the eastern Indian - western Pacific Oceans around Australia , New Guinea and Indonesia .
Acer oblongum , common name Himalayan Maple , Evergreen Maple and Kashmir Maple , is an evergreen Asian species of maple belonging to the soapberry family .
Jasminum officinale , known as the common jasmine or simply jasmine , is a species of flowering plant in the olive family Oleaceae , native to the Caucasus , northern Iran , Afghanistan , Pakistan , the Himalayas , Tajikistan , India , Nepal and western China ( Guizhou , Sichuan , Xizang ( Tibet ) , Yunnan ) .
It contains only one species , Michaeliodes friesei , which is found in Albania and Greece .
Palaemonetes antrorum , also known as the Balcones cave shrimp and the Texas cave shrimp , is a species of palaemonid shrimp endemic to Texas .
Haploesthes robusta is a Mexican species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Graphium browni belongs to the wallacei species group .
Sphagneticola trilobata is listed in the IUCN 's `` List of the world 's 100 worst invasive species '' .
Alangiaceae was recognized as a small family of small dicotyledon trees , shrubs or lianas , closely related to the Cornaceae ( Dogwood family ) .
Alstonia longifolia is a plant species in the genus Alstonia , family Apocynaceae .
Myoxocephalus sinensis is a species of sculpin fish in the family Cottidae .
Acantholycosa pedestris is a wolf spider species in the genus Acantholycosa found in Europe .
Planorbidella depressa is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neomphalidae .
Perissias taeniopterus , the Striped - fin flounder , is a species of lefteye flounder native to the eastern Pacific Ocean along the coast of Central America from Mexico to Panama .
Coptotriche is a genus of moths in the Tischeriidae family .
Gyromitra fastigiata is a species of fungus in the family Discinaceae .
Cynoglossum grande is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Pacific hound 's tongue .
Lambis truncata , common name the giant spider conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
It contains only one species , Abareia amaurodes , which is found in Australia .
Carallia calycina is a species of plant in the Rhizophoraceae family that is endemic to Sri Lanka .
Meiacanthus geminatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean where it is known from Darvel Bay , Borneo and Palawan , Philippines .
Nebria pulcherrima is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that can be found in Chinese province of Jiangxi and Japan .
Pomacea superba is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
Porphyridium cruentum is a species of red alga in the family Porphyridiophyceae .
Haworthia angustifolia is a species of Haworthia from the eastern Cape Province .
Philodromus pardalis is a spider species found in Europe ( Portugal , Spain ) and North Africa ( Algeria to Egypt ) .
Saint Helena ebony ( Trochetiopsis ebenus ) is a species of flowering plant that is endemic to the island of Saint Helena in the southern Atlantic Ocean .
Agkistrodon contortrix is a species of venomous snake endemic to North America , a member of the Crotalinae ( pit viper ) subfamily .
Lithophragma parviflorum is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name smallflower woodland star .
Phrynarachne decipiens , the bird - dropping spider , is a species of tropical crab spider from Malaysia , Sumatra and Java .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Grovesia pulchella .
Festuca amethystina ( Tufted fescue ) is a species of true grass ( Poaceae ) native to Europe , including Turkey .

Neisseria mucosa is a species of Neisseria .
Sphaerantia is a group of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae , described as a genus in 1988 .
Grandopronotalia carnarvona is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Grandopronotalia .
Euprenolepis negrosensis is an ant species that belongs to the Euprenolepis genus .

Tellina tenuis , the thin tellin , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Tellinidae .
Conus nussatella , common name the Nussatella cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Papilio tydeus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in the Moluccas ( Batchian and Gilolo ) .
Betta miniopinna is a species of gourami endemic to Bintan Island in the Riau Archipelago of Indonesia .
Gorgonocephalus arcticus is a species of basket star in the class Ophiuroidea .

Styrax platanifolius is a species of flowering plant in the family Styracaceae known by the common name sycamoreleaf snowbell .
The Melanesian megapode or Melanesian scrubfowl ( Megapodius eremita ) is a species of bird in the Megapodiidae family .

Pleioptygma carolinense is an extinct species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleioptygmatidae .
Sigesbeckia orientalis , known as eastern St Paul's - wort and common St. Paul 's wort , is a species of plant from Asteraceae used in traditional medicine to treat syphilis , leprosy and other skin - related illnesses .
Brassiophoenix is a monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in Papua New Guinea .
Crystallichthys matsushimae is a species of snailfish native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Clathrina aurea is a sponge species of the genus Clathrina from Brazil .
The Paxillosida are a large order of sea stars .
Paphiopedilum appletonianum is a species of orchid occurring from Hainan Island to Indochina .
Poa arachnifera , the Texas bluegrass , is a species of grass .
Corylus colchica is species of hazelnut endemic to Armenia and Georgia in the Caucasus region .
Paradicula setifer is a species of sole known only from the Pacific coast of Australia .
Leucopaxillus is a genus of fairly large white - spored gilled mushrooms which are found worldwide growing on the ground in woodlands .
Russula integra , commonly known as The Entire Russula , is a species of mushroom .
Phthersigena nebulosa is a species of praying mantis native to Australia .
Myrtastrum is a genus of plants in the Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 1941 .
Aeneator galatheae is a species of sea snail , a whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Navigobius is a genus of dartfish native to the Indo - Pacific Ocean .
Crassigyrinus ( meaning `` thick tadpole '' ) is an extinct genus of carnivorous stem tetrapod from the Early Carboniferous of Scotland and possibly Greer , West Virginia .
Gloydius ussuriensis is a venomous pitviper species endemic to far east Russia , northeastern China and the Korean Peninsula .
Niceforo 's pintail ( Anas georgica niceforoi ) is an extinct subspecies of the yellow - billed pintail ( Anas georgica ) , a duck in the dabbling duck subfamily Anatinae .
Persicaria sagittata , common names American tearthumb , arrowleaf tearthumb , or arrowvine , is a plant species widespread in the eastern half of North America as well as in eastern Asia .
Collomia rawsoniana is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name flaming trumpet .
Diorhabda sublineata is a species of leaf beetle known as the subtropical tamarisk beetle ( STB ) which feeds on tamarisk trees from Portugal , Spain and France to Morocco , Senegal , Algeria , Tunisia , Egypt , Yemen , and Iraq .
Oxycera terminata , the yellow - tipped soldierr , is a European species of soldier fly .
Farlowella acus is the type species of a genus of armored catfish commonly known as the twig catfish or whiptail catfish .
Cacibupteryx is a genus of rhamphorhynchid `` rhamphorhynchoid '' pterosaur from the middle - late Oxfordian - age Upper Jurassic Jagua Formation of Pinar del Río , Cuba .

Mystacinidae is a family of unusual bats , the New Zealand short - tailed bats .
Cymatoderma elegans is a fungus species in the genus Cymatoderma .
Horshamosaurus is a genus of herbivorous ankylosaurian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of England .
Chrysactinia truncata , is a Mexican species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Leopardus is a genus of small spotted cats mostly native to Middle and South America .
Shuotheriidae is a small Mesozoic family of mammals whose remains are found in China .
Dendrerpeton is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Carboniferous of Nova Scotia .
Chamaesyce is a former genus of plants each of which has now been reclassified as being Euphorbia .
Tanakaea radicans or the Japanese foam flower , is a member of the Saxifrage family native to Japan , and is the sole species in the genus Tanakaea .
Prosopis laevigata , commonly known as smooth mesquite , is a species of flowering tree in the pea family , Fabaceae family , that is native to Mexico , Bolivia , Peru , and northwestern Argentina ( Jujuy Province ) .
Geranium aculeolatum is a herbaceous plant species in the Geraniaceae family .
Pnigomantis medioconstricta common name Indonesian double shield mantis or double shield mantis are the only species in the genus Pnigomantis of mantis of the family Mantidae .
The Oklahoma salamander ( Eurycea tynerensis ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to the United States .
Cyperus laevigatus is a species of sedge known by the common name smooth flatsedge .

Viola tripartita is a species of violet known by the common name threepart violet .
Sphenacanthus is an extinct genus of a chondrichtyan xenacanthiform that belongs to the Sphenacanthidae family and lived during the Carboniferous periodo in Scotland , Spain , Russia and Brazil .
Digitaria ciliaris is a species of grass known by the common names southern crabgrass , tropical finger - grass , tropical crabgrass or summer grass .
The Formosan black bear ( 臺灣黑熊 , Ursus thibetanus formosanus , or Selenarctos thibetanus formosanus ) , also known as the white - throated bear , is a subspecies of the Asiatic black bear .
Chroniosaurus is an extinct genus of chroniosuchid reptiliomorph from upper Permian ( upper Tatarian age ) deposits of Novgorod , Orenburg and Vologda Regions , Russia .

Potamopyrgus is a genus of minute freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the family Tateidae .

Ammagnostidae is a family of trilobites in the suborder Agnostina , small , eyeless , isopygous trilobites with a thorax consisting of 2 segments only .
Calliostoma atlantis , common name the Atlantis top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .

Saccopteryx is a genus of sac - winged bats from Central and South America .

Photis conchicola is a species of marine amphipod crustacean which lives in the Eastern Pacific Ocean .

Glaniopsis is a small genus of loaches endemic to the island of Borneo .

Eucharis astrophiala is a species of plant which is endemic to Ecuador .
